WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:09.020
 Roth, Book 4 of the Faithful and the Fallen, by John Gwynn, read by Damien Lynch.

00:00:09.020 --> 00:00:17.160
 Roth and vengeance poured, John Milton, Paradise Lost.

00:00:17.160 --> 00:00:23.000
 Chapter 1 There it is.

00:00:23.000 --> 00:00:30.000
 The year 1144 of the Age of Exiles, Hound moon.

00:00:30.000 --> 00:00:34.000
 There it is, fell through the night air, weightless.

00:00:34.000 --> 00:00:37.000
 He caught glimpses of the Tower of Bricken.

00:00:37.000 --> 00:00:43.000
 Caledas is still smoldering outline at the window, then below, the river coming up to meet him.

00:00:43.000 --> 00:00:47.000
 He slammed into the water, the cold shocking the breath out of him.

00:00:47.000 --> 00:00:52.000
 He panicked, disorientated, realizing he didn't know which way was up.

00:00:52.000 --> 00:00:55.000
 All about him was darkness and ice.

00:00:55.000 --> 00:01:02.000
 Then something grabbed his hair, and he was surging upwards, breaking through the water in a burst of spray,

00:01:02.000 --> 00:01:06.000
 and saw Alsion's pale broad face staring back at him.

00:01:06.000 --> 00:01:13.000
 "They will come hunting for us," the giant shouted over the roar of the river, as the current gripped them,

00:01:13.000 --> 00:01:17.000
 sweeping them away from the thunder of warriors' feet crossing the bridge.

00:01:17.000 --> 00:01:21.000
 "Let the water take us far from them."

00:01:21.000 --> 00:01:27.000
 Verida saw the sense of that, though his hands and feet were already numbing from the cold.

00:01:27.000 --> 00:01:34.000
 He put some effort into swimming, speeding his way from Bricken, from Caledas, from the Qadashim.

00:01:34.000 --> 00:01:38.000
 The thought still jolted him like a blow.

00:01:38.000 --> 00:01:44.000
 They turned a bend in the river, and the fortress was gone, darkness in folding them.

00:01:44.000 --> 00:01:53.000
 The soft weak sheen of dawn's gray light filtered down through the lattice of branches above, as Verida's met Alsion's gaze,

00:01:53.000 --> 00:01:59.000
 an unspoken agreement passing between them, as they both headed for the river back.

00:01:59.000 --> 00:02:05.000
 It was harder going, swimming across the current, and Verida's realized how exhausted his body was,

00:02:05.000 --> 00:02:12.000
 but eventually he felt silt beneath his feet, his hands grasping at reeds as he pulled himself out of the water,

00:02:12.000 --> 00:02:17.000
 and flopped onto his back, gasping, his limbs feeling lead-filled.

00:02:17.000 --> 00:02:20.000
 Turning, he saw Alsion on the bank.

00:02:20.000 --> 00:02:27.000
 Thirty of forty paces up river from him, staggering wearily towards him before he slumped down beside him with a groan,

00:02:27.000 --> 00:02:30.000
 water dripping from his drooping moustache.

00:02:30.000 --> 00:02:34.000
 "Thank you," Alsion said.

00:02:34.000 --> 00:02:36.000
 "For what?"

00:02:36.000 --> 00:02:37.000
 "Everything.

00:02:37.000 --> 00:02:41.000
 Most of all, for helping my family escape Bricken's dungeons.

00:02:41.000 --> 00:02:44.000
 His wife and bern.

00:02:44.000 --> 00:02:47.000
 How long has he gone without seeing them?

00:02:47.000 --> 00:02:52.000
 And what must he have suffered, knowing they were Caledus and Lycosy's prisoners?

00:02:52.000 --> 00:02:57.000
 And for destroying Caledus's effigy of me?"

00:02:57.000 --> 00:03:01.000
 Alsion continued, "You have set me free."

00:03:01.000 --> 00:03:05.000
 He gave a shudder, followed by a smile.

00:03:05.000 --> 00:03:09.000
 "A shadow is gone from my soul.

00:03:09.000 --> 00:03:11.000
 I feel reborn."

00:03:11.000 --> 00:03:15.000
 "If you mean you feel weak as a newborn bern,"

00:03:15.000 --> 00:03:19.000
 Veridus muttered as he emptied his boot of water and tried to pull it back on.

00:03:19.000 --> 00:03:21.000
 "Then I feel the same."

00:03:21.000 --> 00:03:25.000
 "That is not what I mean," the giant rumbled,

00:03:25.000 --> 00:03:28.000
 regarding Veridus with serious eyes.

00:03:28.000 --> 00:03:31.000
 "You set Rainer and Tane free."

00:03:31.000 --> 00:03:34.000
 "You set me free."

00:03:34.000 --> 00:03:37.000
 "I owe you a deck beyond all imagining."

00:03:37.000 --> 00:03:42.000
 "You are in no debt to me," Veridus said.

00:03:42.000 --> 00:03:45.000
 "I kick the effigy's into the fire on impulse,

00:03:45.000 --> 00:03:49.000
 not really knowing what they were or what power they held over you."

00:03:49.000 --> 00:03:51.000
 "But you suspected."

00:03:51.000 --> 00:03:52.000
 "I."

00:03:52.000 --> 00:03:56.000
 "Something that Fidele said."

00:03:56.000 --> 00:04:00.000
 He thought of Nithair's mother, hoped that she had made it to freedom

00:04:00.000 --> 00:04:05.000
 along with his brother, Krelis, McIn, and Halbin.

00:04:05.000 --> 00:04:10.000
 And your wife and son, I set them free because it was the right thing to do."

00:04:10.000 --> 00:04:13.000
 "There was no other choice."

00:04:13.000 --> 00:04:17.000
 "Ah, but there was true heart.

00:04:17.000 --> 00:04:20.000
 There always is."

00:04:20.000 --> 00:04:22.000
 Veridus shrugged.

00:04:22.000 --> 00:04:24.000
 "There is no debt between us."

00:04:24.000 --> 00:04:27.000
 "You are my friend."

00:04:27.000 --> 00:04:30.000
 "One of my only friends," it has turned out.

00:04:30.000 --> 00:04:33.000
 His thoughts swept bitterly to Nithair,

00:04:33.000 --> 00:04:37.000
 and the confession and revelations that had stunned Veridus.

00:04:37.000 --> 00:04:40.000
 He remembered Calidus's confession.

00:04:40.000 --> 00:04:45.000
 That Nithair had slain Aquilis, his own father.

00:04:45.000 --> 00:04:48.000
 Anger and shame twisted through him.

00:04:48.000 --> 00:04:51.000
 "There had been so many signs."

00:04:51.000 --> 00:04:55.000
 "How can I have been deceived for so long?"

00:04:55.000 --> 00:04:57.000
 "I am a fool."

00:04:57.000 --> 00:04:59.000
 "How long?"

00:04:59.000 --> 00:05:01.000
 Veridus asked him.

00:05:01.000 --> 00:05:04.000
 "How long have you been Calidus's prisoner?"

00:05:04.000 --> 00:05:07.000
 Alcyon smiled with it.

00:05:07.000 --> 00:05:10.000
 "Sixteen years."

00:05:10.000 --> 00:05:13.000
 "That is a long time."

00:05:13.000 --> 00:05:15.000
 "It is."

00:05:15.000 --> 00:05:18.000
 Alcyon clenched his fists, knuckles cracking.

00:05:18.000 --> 00:05:21.000
 "I should have killed him."

00:05:21.000 --> 00:05:25.000
 "To be fair, we both tried hard on that count.

00:05:25.000 --> 00:05:28.000
 I put a knife in his belly, threw him in a fire,

00:05:28.000 --> 00:05:31.000
 and he shattered his chest with a wall hammer.

00:05:31.000 --> 00:05:34.000
 "Cadoshim are hard to kill.

00:05:34.000 --> 00:05:36.000
 I'd have to agree.

00:05:36.000 --> 00:05:38.000
 Can he be killed?"

00:05:38.000 --> 00:05:41.000
 "Maybe taking his head."

00:05:41.000 --> 00:05:44.000
 "That is how the others are slain.

00:05:44.000 --> 00:05:45.000
 Others?"

00:05:45.000 --> 00:05:52.000
 Alcyon said to the question in Veridus's eyes.

00:05:52.000 --> 00:06:00.000
 "The Geeha," Veridus muttered, shaking his head.

00:06:00.000 --> 00:06:03.000
 "I've been so blind."

00:06:03.000 --> 00:06:08.000
 "You trusted your king and your friend."

00:06:08.000 --> 00:06:10.000
 Alcyon shrugged.

00:06:10.000 --> 00:06:13.000
 "There are worse failings to have."

00:06:13.000 --> 00:06:16.000
 "Are there?"

00:06:16.000 --> 00:06:20.000
 "I have dedicated my life to a lie."

00:06:20.000 --> 00:06:25.000
 "They both sat in silence, water dripping from clothes and hair."

00:06:25.000 --> 00:06:27.000
 "What now?"

00:06:27.000 --> 00:06:29.000
 Veridus said to himself.

00:06:29.000 --> 00:06:34.000
 "It feels as if my whole life has been dedicated to an affair in his cause."

00:06:34.000 --> 00:06:37.000
 "What do I do now?"

00:06:37.000 --> 00:06:41.000
 Alcyon regarded him gravely, and poked his chest with a thick finger.

00:06:41.000 --> 00:06:45.000
 "What does your heart tell you?"

00:06:45.000 --> 00:06:47.000
 "I will not trust it."

00:06:47.000 --> 00:06:50.000
 "Look, Veridus led me thus far."

00:06:50.000 --> 00:06:52.000
 Veridus said, "Sowling.

00:06:52.000 --> 00:06:55.000
 Your eyes are open now."

00:06:55.000 --> 00:07:01.000
 Veridus sucked in a deep breath, felt exhaustion seeping through him.

00:07:01.000 --> 00:07:03.000
 "What would you do?"

00:07:03.000 --> 00:07:05.000
 He asked the giant.

00:07:05.000 --> 00:07:10.000
 "Find my kin, my reina, and tain."

00:07:10.000 --> 00:07:13.000
 He smiled as he said their names.

00:07:13.000 --> 00:07:15.000
 "Kin."

00:07:15.000 --> 00:07:17.000
 "My father is slain."

00:07:17.000 --> 00:07:19.000
 "That is my brother, Ector."

00:07:19.000 --> 00:07:21.000
 "Only Krellus is left."

00:07:21.000 --> 00:07:25.000
 Suddenly he was desperate to see his older brother.

00:07:25.000 --> 00:07:28.000
 "Find our kin," he echoed.

00:07:28.000 --> 00:07:32.000
 "A good place to start."

00:07:32.000 --> 00:07:34.000
 "Something squawked."

00:07:34.000 --> 00:07:39.000
 A handful of wood pigeons suddenly bursting from the trees and flapping noisily overhead.

00:07:39.000 --> 00:07:41.000
 "We should move."

00:07:41.000 --> 00:07:42.000
 "We need cover."

00:07:42.000 --> 00:07:43.000
 "I."

00:07:43.000 --> 00:07:44.000
 "To the trees."

00:07:44.000 --> 00:07:48.000
 Veridus said, as he stood suppressing a groan.

00:07:48.000 --> 00:07:54.000
 They were halfway across the clearing when Alcyon stopped abruptly, staring back along the riverbank.

00:07:54.000 --> 00:07:57.000
 Forms appeared around a distant bend on the track.

00:07:57.000 --> 00:08:01.000
 Shadows in the half-light that forms canopy created.

00:08:01.000 --> 00:08:05.000
 Black shadows with curved swords sheath across their backs.

00:08:05.000 --> 00:08:07.000
 "Kado Shem."

00:08:07.000 --> 00:08:09.000
 Alcyon growled.

00:08:09.000 --> 00:08:16.000
 Veridus counted at least seven of them, moving quickly, a low-pin ground-eating paste like a pack of wolfen.

00:08:16.000 --> 00:08:21.000
 They were spread in a half-circle between the riverbank and the tree-line.

00:08:21.000 --> 00:08:23.000
 They are hunting us.

00:08:23.000 --> 00:08:28.000
 They have been running all night long following the river in search of our trail.

00:08:28.000 --> 00:08:33.000
 One of the figures paused, the others rippling to a halt about it.

00:08:33.000 --> 00:08:42.000
 It lifted its head as if tasting the air, then gave an allulating howl and leapt forwards a new energy in its stride.

00:08:42.000 --> 00:08:45.000
 They've caught our scent.

00:08:45.000 --> 00:08:48.000
 Veridus felt a jolt of fear.

00:08:48.000 --> 00:08:57.000
 He'd faced giants, dregs, war bands, but somehow knowing that the deans of the other world were hunting him sent a cold shock of fear tingling through his veins.

00:08:57.000 --> 00:09:14.000
 Kalidus filled his mind, an image of the man he had thought Counsellor and ally emerging from the fire in Brickann's tower, flaying reaved and snarling.

00:09:14.000 --> 00:09:18.000
 He has corrupted Nefair and has deceived me for so long.

00:09:18.000 --> 00:09:22.000
 He is the author of this evil.

00:09:22.000 --> 00:09:27.000
 Fear morphed into a cold rage and he reached for his sword, lips twisting.

00:09:27.000 --> 00:09:28.000
 Move.

00:09:28.000 --> 00:09:32.000
 Alcyon grunted and broke into a run.

00:09:32.000 --> 00:09:42.000
 Veridus resisted for a moment, inexplicably wanting to stand and flank these creatures, but Alcyon dragged him along and in a heartbeat, they were only a few strides from the tree-line.

00:09:42.000 --> 00:09:46.000
 He realized the giant had no weapon.

00:09:46.000 --> 00:09:51.000
 No war hammer or battle-like strapped across his back, no sword or dagger at his hip.

00:09:51.000 --> 00:09:59.000
 They crashed through the first layer of undergrowth and were immediately enveloped by a twilight world of shadow and thorn.

00:09:59.000 --> 00:10:10.000
 Alcyon forged ahead, grunting as branches snapped upon his rock-like torso, thorns whipping at Veridus, vines tangling about his boots.

00:10:10.000 --> 00:10:19.000
 For it seemed a long time, Veridus only heard his own heart thumping the rasp of his breath, the thud of Alcyon's feet.

00:10:19.000 --> 00:10:28.000
 Then there were sounds behind him, faint at first, like the rustle of wind through foliage, but soon louder, keening cries were floating about him.

00:10:28.000 --> 00:10:37.000
 They splashed through a string, something sinuous slivered beneath Veridus's feet, making him stumble.

00:10:37.000 --> 00:10:41.000
 "They are almost upon us," he gasped to Alcyon.

00:10:41.000 --> 00:10:46.000
 Better to turn and fight, hold a sword in my fist than die running.

00:10:46.000 --> 00:10:51.000
 "I know," the giant said, turning, chest-heaving.

00:10:51.000 --> 00:10:57.000
 Veridus drew his sword as they put their backs to a huge tree, the stream before them, and waited.

00:10:57.000 --> 00:11:03.000
 Forms flitted through the gloom, emerging from a curtain of shadows and thick foliage.

00:11:03.000 --> 00:11:13.000
 One was a long way ahead of the others, clothed in the dark male of the Jihar, pale-skinned, dark veins making a tapestry of its flesh.

00:11:13.000 --> 00:11:19.000
 It saw them and leapt the stream, arms reaching for Veridus, not even bothering to draw its sword.

00:11:19.000 --> 00:11:30.000
 "Remember, you must take their heads," Alcyon grunted, as he pushed away from the tree, hurling himself into the oncoming catachim with bone-crushing power.

00:11:30.000 --> 00:11:33.000
 The two fell to the ground.

00:11:33.000 --> 00:11:38.000
 Veridus hurtled forwards, sword raised, hacking two-handed at the catachim's arm.

00:11:38.000 --> 00:11:43.000
 Its hand spinning away, blood like oil, pumping languidly from the stump.

00:11:43.000 --> 00:11:46.000
 Then the two forms were rolling together again.

00:11:46.000 --> 00:11:49.000
 Alcyon ground in pain, then he was on his knees.

00:11:49.000 --> 00:11:54.000
 Arms wrapped about the catachim's torso, pinning its arms at its side.

00:11:54.000 --> 00:11:58.000
 The creature's head rived, veins bulging as it strained to break free.

00:11:58.000 --> 00:12:03.000
 Alcyon's face turning purple with the effort, his locked fingers slowly pulling apart.

00:12:03.000 --> 00:12:09.000
 "What are you waiting for?" the giant rasped.

00:12:09.000 --> 00:12:13.000
 And Veridus swung his sword, chopping into the creature's neck.

00:12:13.000 --> 00:12:18.000
 Dark blood spurted from the half-severed neck, the catachim's screeching with fury.

00:12:18.000 --> 00:12:21.000
 Alcyon roared with the strain of holding the creature.

00:12:21.000 --> 00:12:26.000
 Veridus ranged his sword free, and swung again.

00:12:26.000 --> 00:12:31.000
 The catachim's head flew through the air landing with a splash in the stream.

00:12:31.000 --> 00:12:37.000
 Its body slumped, legs drumming as Alcyon fell away and rolled clear.

00:12:37.000 --> 00:12:46.000
 A black eye-core-like mist flowed from the catachim's neck, hissing and swirling, gathering above its body,

00:12:46.000 --> 00:12:51.000
 forming a human shape with tattered wings of smoke spread about it and red eyes glowing like

00:12:51.000 --> 00:12:53.000
 colds at its heart.

00:12:53.000 --> 00:12:55.000
 Veridus stared.

00:12:55.000 --> 00:12:56.000
 Frozen.

00:12:56.000 --> 00:13:02.000
 It screamed savagely, then it was melting away, torn and dispersed by a slight breeze.

00:13:02.000 --> 00:13:05.000
 "What the hell?" Veridus gasped.

00:13:05.000 --> 00:13:11.000
 "Down!" Alcyon yelled, as he surged up from the ground, a fist slamming into the jaw

00:13:11.000 --> 00:13:16.000
 of a leaping catachim, hurling its spinning into the undergrowth.

00:13:16.000 --> 00:13:22.000
 Almost as soon as it hit the ground, it was back on its feet, twisting like a feral cat.

00:13:22.000 --> 00:13:34.000
 Veridus hefted his sword, spread his legs to meet the impact, and then something crunched into his side, sending him flying through the air another catachim's arms locked around his waist.

00:13:34.000 --> 00:13:41.000
 He caught a glimpse of Alcyon's standing, catachim's swarming upon him, then Veridus was slamming into the ground.

00:13:41.000 --> 00:13:46.000
 Pain exploded in his shoulder, and his sword skitted away.

00:13:46.000 --> 00:13:55.000
 He rolled, punched at his attacker, for a moment staring into its black, soulless eyes, then they were sliding into the stream that catachim beneath him,

00:13:55.000 --> 00:14:01.000
 his hands fastening about its neck, squeezing, seeking to crush the life from the black-eyed abomination.

00:14:01.000 --> 00:14:10.000
 It bucked and kicked like a wild stallion, thrashing a tempest amidst the streamwater, but Veridus would not let go.

00:14:10.000 --> 00:14:21.000
 He felt its strength ebbing, some of its vitality fading, then hands gripped him from behind, dragging him backwards, his fingers slipping as he was hauled to the bank.

00:14:21.000 --> 00:14:28.000
 Another catachim stood over him, drawing its sword from its back as the one from the stream splashed into view.

00:14:28.000 --> 00:14:35.000
 He rolled and saw a handful of catachim circling Alcyon, who had fallen to one knee, the giant bleeding from a dozen wounds.

00:14:35.000 --> 00:14:39.000
 Veridus tried to drag himself through the mud towards his friend.

00:14:39.000 --> 00:14:46.000
 Another catachim was held in Alcyon's arms, he had one hand gripping its jaw, the other wrapped about its chest.

00:14:46.000 --> 00:14:49.000
 With a savage wrench, Alcyon heaved.

00:14:49.000 --> 00:14:57.000
 Veridus heard the catachim's neck break, then the sound of flesh tearing, Alcyon screaming his defiance as he ripped the catachim's head from its shoulders.

00:14:57.000 --> 00:15:02.000
 He flung the corpse to the ground as the black mist boiled from the dead creature's wound.

00:15:02.000 --> 00:15:09.000
 The searing pain lance through Veridus' leg, a catachim blade scoring along his thigh.

00:15:09.000 --> 00:15:13.000
 He dropped to the ground, looked back at the two catachim on the stream bank.

00:15:13.000 --> 00:15:17.000
 They were following him, toying with him.

00:15:17.000 --> 00:15:25.000
 The one with a drawn sword slashed his blade across Veridus' uphill forearm, and you cut burning like fire.

00:15:25.000 --> 00:15:33.000
 "Think, will, bleed you a while," the catachim said, layering with pale lips.

00:15:33.000 --> 00:15:37.000
 "Pay you back for the chase you've led us."

00:15:37.000 --> 00:15:40.000
 It should not end like this.

00:15:40.000 --> 00:15:47.000
 Frustration gave Veridus a last surge of strength, and he rolled to his feet, pushed himself upright.

00:15:47.000 --> 00:15:53.000
 The catachim before him grinned, then paused, cocking its head to one side.

00:15:53.000 --> 00:15:56.000
 The figures burst out of the gloom.

00:15:56.000 --> 00:16:04.000
 Veridus' hopes rose in then fell, as he saw the newcomers were dressed in black breastplates with silver eagles on their chests.

00:16:04.000 --> 00:16:05.000
 Eagle guard.

00:16:05.000 --> 00:16:10.000
 No doubt said by Nefair to make sure that his monsters complete their task.

00:16:10.000 --> 00:16:11.000
 10.

00:16:11.000 --> 00:16:12.000
 12.

00:16:12.000 --> 00:16:17.000
 15 more men, one of them tall and wide.

00:16:17.000 --> 00:16:19.000
 Veridus blinked.

00:16:19.000 --> 00:16:21.000
 Something familiar.

00:16:21.000 --> 00:16:27.000
 Well met, little brother, the big man bellowed, grinning wildly.

00:16:27.000 --> 00:16:32.000
 A moment's confusion followed swiftly by elation.

00:16:32.000 --> 00:16:34.000
 "Crellas!"

00:16:34.000 --> 00:16:41.000
 Then Crellas and his men were attacking the catachim, Crellas taking their head in one great swing of his longsword.

00:16:41.000 --> 00:16:44.000
 Another warrior swept into view.

00:16:44.000 --> 00:16:49.000
 This one not dressed as a man of tenor brow, but gripping a knife in each hand.

00:16:49.000 --> 00:16:54.000
 He joined Crellas, and together they attacked the catachim before Veridus.

00:16:54.000 --> 00:16:55.000
 14.

00:16:55.000 --> 00:16:58.000
 Macquine and Crellas.

00:16:58.000 --> 00:17:02.000
 22.

00:17:02.000 --> 00:17:05.000
 Nefair

00:17:05.000 --> 00:17:11.000
 Nefair stood in the great hall of Drasil, and stared at the giant skeletonite's throne.

00:17:11.000 --> 00:17:18.000
 The bones of the ribcage surrounded a thick shafted spear, the wood, dark and pale vain.

00:17:18.000 --> 00:17:21.000
 Only a hint of black iron of the blade visible.

00:17:21.000 --> 00:17:25.000
 The rest buried in the great tree of Drasil.

00:17:25.000 --> 00:17:27.000
 So that is scald.

00:17:27.000 --> 00:17:32.000
 High king of the giants, and that is the starstone spear.

00:17:32.000 --> 00:17:33.000
 Scald.

00:17:33.000 --> 00:17:39.000
 The last man to rule a united empire where giants and men live together in peace.

00:17:39.000 --> 00:17:43.000
 Will I be the next to unite this shattered world?

00:17:43.000 --> 00:17:48.000
 The skeleton was mottled yellow and brown, ancient.

00:17:48.000 --> 00:17:53.000
 The brow of the skull broad and thick eye sockets, black holes that seemed to stare

00:17:53.000 --> 00:17:56.000
 at the fair, questioning him.

00:17:56.000 --> 00:17:58.000
 Are you worthy?

00:17:58.000 --> 00:18:00.000
 Are you capable?

00:18:00.000 --> 00:18:02.000
 He sighed.

00:18:02.000 --> 00:18:07.000
 History shall be my judge, nothing and no one else.

00:18:07.000 --> 00:18:10.000
 The hand touched his shoulder.

00:18:10.000 --> 00:18:16.000
