 The thoughts rose unbidden in her mind.

00:37:19.000 --> 00:37:24.000
 The one thought she'd refuse to acknowledge throughout the long dark of night.

00:37:24.000 --> 00:37:27.000
 What if he is slain?

00:37:27.000 --> 00:37:31.000
 What else could have kept him from returning to Drassel?

00:37:31.000 --> 00:37:36.000
 She felt a worm of fear wriggling through her belly, but refused to consider it.

00:37:36.000 --> 00:37:38.000
 He lives.

00:37:38.000 --> 00:37:40.000
 He must.

00:37:40.000 --> 00:37:42.000
 She nodded, and stood.

00:37:42.000 --> 00:37:48.000
 She leaving her knife, a myriad of cuts, bruises, and strains, aching for attention.

00:37:48.000 --> 00:37:50.000
 She ignored them all.

00:37:50.000 --> 00:37:54.000
 "We need to go," she said.

00:37:54.000 --> 00:37:57.000
 "I." Gah agreed.

00:37:57.000 --> 00:38:01.000
 He continued to stare at the trapdoor.

00:38:01.000 --> 00:38:06.000
 I had hoped that my cow would find us, that he escaped."

00:38:06.000 --> 00:38:09.000
 Corinne remembered her last sight of the Ben-Elim.

00:38:09.000 --> 00:38:18.000
 Wielding his sword, two-handed, feet planted before the entrance to the tunnel in Drassel's great hall as they had retreated into its shadows.

00:38:18.000 --> 00:38:28.000
 Swayves of blood had surrounded him as he swung his sword in deadly arcs, holding back the enemy, protecting them, purchasing them time to escape.

00:38:28.000 --> 00:38:31.000
 He would come by now, if he could.

00:38:31.000 --> 00:38:33.000
 Corinne said.

00:38:33.000 --> 00:38:36.000
 Gah sighed and nodded.

00:38:36.000 --> 00:38:41.000
 Corinne cocked her head, listening, staring down the hill.

00:38:41.000 --> 00:38:45.000
 Something was moving in the undergrowth, heading towards the trapdoor.

00:38:45.000 --> 00:38:53.000
 Gah saw it too, and without words the two of them separated, slipping into the shadows as they quietly surrounded the intruder.

00:38:53.000 --> 00:38:59.000
 Bushes rustled, a twig snapped, and Corinne caught a glimpse of dark hair.

00:38:59.000 --> 00:39:04.000
 She knew he wasn't Corinne, even he isn't that clumsy.

00:39:04.000 --> 00:39:06.000
 A figure burst from the undergrowth.

00:39:06.000 --> 00:39:14.000
 A young man clad in leather and wool, his dark hair, tousled, and a scabbing cut marking his forehead.

00:39:14.000 --> 00:39:19.000
 He started at the sight of her, fumbled for a weapon at his belt, his eye is widening.

00:39:19.000 --> 00:39:25.000
 "I know you," Corinne said, though she didn't remember his name.

00:39:25.000 --> 00:39:28.000
 "Your da is itilius."

00:39:28.000 --> 00:39:35.000
 A competent, unassuming warrior, itilius had been a slave oarsman on a Vinth Island ship.

00:39:35.000 --> 00:39:37.000
 The lad nodded.

00:39:37.000 --> 00:39:39.000
 His lip trembling.

00:39:39.000 --> 00:39:42.000
 "Pax, what are you doing here?"

00:39:42.000 --> 00:39:48.000
 Gah said, stepping silently from the shadows, making the young warrior jump again.

00:39:48.000 --> 00:39:50.000
 "You must come quickly."

00:39:50.000 --> 00:39:51.000
 Pax blurted.

00:39:51.000 --> 00:39:52.000
 "My da.

00:39:52.000 --> 00:39:53.000
 Corbin.

00:39:53.000 --> 00:39:54.000
 Giants."

00:39:54.000 --> 00:39:55.000
 "Corbin?"

00:39:55.000 --> 00:39:56.000
 Corinne hissed.

00:39:56.000 --> 00:39:57.000
 "I.

00:39:57.000 --> 00:39:59.000
 We must go."

00:39:59.000 --> 00:40:05.000
 Tears were spilling down Pax's cheeks now, tracing tracks through blood and grime.

00:40:05.000 --> 00:40:07.000
 He stared.

00:40:07.000 --> 00:40:12.000
 Corinne froze, feeling as if a fist had just clamped around her heart.

00:40:12.000 --> 00:40:14.000
 "I ran."

00:40:14.000 --> 00:40:16.000
 Pax said.

00:40:16.000 --> 00:40:21.000
 "He began to shake, an involuntary twitching that quickly became more violent."

00:40:21.000 --> 00:40:24.000
 "Where is Corbin?"

00:40:24.000 --> 00:40:28.960
 Corinne asked, trying to control the panic leaking through her, reaching out to grab the

00:40:28.960 --> 00:40:32.000
 now sobbing boy and shake the sense from him.

00:40:32.000 --> 00:40:37.000
 "Hold," Gah said, putting a hand upon her arm.

00:40:37.000 --> 00:40:40.000
 "Pax, you must tell us as clearly as you can.

00:40:40.000 --> 00:40:42.000
 Where is Corbin and your da?

00:40:42.000 --> 00:40:44.000
 What happened?"

00:40:44.000 --> 00:40:46.000
 "Others were coming down the hill now."

00:40:46.000 --> 00:40:52.000
 Corinne glimpsed daff in colour, a handful of jihad, lathe looming behind them.

00:40:52.000 --> 00:40:53.000
 "We heard.

00:40:53.000 --> 00:40:54.000
 Fighting.

00:40:54.000 --> 00:40:56.000
 New Corbin was out there."

00:40:56.000 --> 00:40:57.000
 Pax began, haltingly.

00:40:57.000 --> 00:41:00.000
 "We found him, facing giants and bears."

00:41:00.000 --> 00:41:01.000
 "What?"

00:41:01.000 --> 00:41:04.000
 "But there were no giants in the fair at Dressel."

00:41:04.000 --> 00:41:05.000
 "Dah.

00:41:05.000 --> 00:41:08.000
 He threw a spear at a giant.

00:41:08.000 --> 00:41:09.000
 Then we all ran.

00:41:09.000 --> 00:41:10.000
 We thought we'd lost them.

00:41:10.000 --> 00:41:11.000
 Then..."

00:41:11.000 --> 00:41:13.000
 "Go on," Gah said.

00:41:13.000 --> 00:41:18.000
 The whole group was gathered around them now, listing in absolute silence.

00:41:18.000 --> 00:41:21.000
 "They came from nowhere.

00:41:21.000 --> 00:41:23.000
 My da?"

00:41:23.000 --> 00:41:28.000
 He rubbed his eyes, blew out a long breath.

00:41:28.000 --> 00:41:31.000
 "They killed my da."

00:41:31.000 --> 00:41:34.000
 Corbin told me to run to fetch help.

00:41:34.000 --> 00:41:36.000
 "When did this happen?"

00:41:36.000 --> 00:41:40.000
 Gah asked, not able to keep the urgency from his voice.

00:41:40.000 --> 00:41:44.000
 "Yesterday, after his son before, sunset."

00:41:44.000 --> 00:41:47.000
 Pax's face had grown paler as he spoke.

00:41:47.000 --> 00:41:49.000
 "Now he looked like a corpse.

00:41:49.000 --> 00:41:50.000
 I ran.

00:41:50.000 --> 00:41:53.000
 I fell, hit my head."

00:41:53.000 --> 00:41:56.000
 He raised the hand to the cut on his brow.

00:41:56.000 --> 00:41:58.000
 "When I came to?"

00:41:58.000 --> 00:41:59.000
 It was dark.

00:41:59.000 --> 00:42:02.000
 "I've been trying to find my way since then."

00:42:02.000 --> 00:42:03.000
 "Take us.

00:42:03.000 --> 00:42:05.000
 Now," Gah said.

00:42:05.000 --> 00:42:06.000
 "I will try."

00:42:06.000 --> 00:42:07.000
 Pax nodded.

00:42:07.000 --> 00:42:09.000
 I became lost for a while.

00:42:09.000 --> 00:42:12.000
 But I know it was that direction."

00:42:12.000 --> 00:42:15.000
 Gah barked orders and then they were moving.

00:42:15.000 --> 00:42:17.000
 Corbin taking the lead with Pax,

00:42:17.000 --> 00:42:21.000
 Gah jogging beside the ladder, steadying hand on his arm.

00:42:21.000 --> 00:42:24.000
 Corbin stormed, facing giants.

00:42:24.000 --> 00:42:25.000
 Alone.

00:42:25.000 --> 00:42:27.000
 Yesterday.

00:42:27.000 --> 00:42:30.000
 She sent a silent prayer to Elion,

00:42:30.000 --> 00:42:33.000
 one of many that she had made over the last half day.

00:42:33.000 --> 00:42:37.000
 "Let them still live."

00:42:37.000 --> 00:42:40.000
 Corbin was the first to enter the glade.

00:42:40.000 --> 00:42:42.000
 At its far end was a sudden ridge,

00:42:42.000 --> 00:42:45.000
 and beyond it, the sound of a fast flowing river.

00:42:45.000 --> 00:42:47.000
 The smell hit her first.

00:42:47.000 --> 00:42:50.000
 The metallic tang of blood and decay.

00:42:50.000 --> 00:42:52.000
 Death.

00:42:52.000 --> 00:42:54.000
 Flies were buzzing in great clouds

00:42:54.000 --> 00:42:57.000
 about bodies heaped on the floor.

00:42:57.000 --> 00:43:00.000
 She counted three giant corpses on the ground,

00:43:00.000 --> 00:43:04.000
 and Attilius pinned to a great oak by a giant's axe.

00:43:04.000 --> 00:43:07.000
 She could not see Corbin or storm.

00:43:07.000 --> 00:43:09.000
 She ran to the first giant,

00:43:09.000 --> 00:43:11.000
 who was on his back, a hole in his belly,

00:43:11.000 --> 00:43:12.000
 throat cleanly cut,

00:43:12.000 --> 00:43:17.000
 his wrist bearing the tail tail ripping wounds of the wolfen.

00:43:17.000 --> 00:43:19.000
 Corbin moved on,

00:43:19.000 --> 00:43:22.000
 dimly aware of others spilling into the glade behind her,

00:43:22.000 --> 00:43:25.000
 the sound of Pax's sobs as he dropped to his knees before his dark,

00:43:25.000 --> 00:43:28.000
 Gah's presence at her shoulder.

00:43:28.000 --> 00:43:31.000
 The other two giants were close together.

00:43:31.000 --> 00:43:36.000
 The ground trampled, rutted, dark and still sticky with blood.

00:43:36.000 --> 00:43:39.000
 One's throat had been ripped out by storm,

00:43:39.000 --> 00:43:42.000
 the flesh mangled and torn.

00:43:42.000 --> 00:43:46.000
 Here's not here, nor storm.

00:43:46.000 --> 00:43:48.000
 The relief was a physical thing,

00:43:48.000 --> 00:43:50.000
 though she knew their absence did not mean

00:43:50.000 --> 00:43:52.000
 that they were safe for even alive,

00:43:52.000 --> 00:43:55.000
 but it was clear they had fought here and won.

00:43:55.000 --> 00:43:58.000
 They slew three giants.

00:43:58.000 --> 00:44:01.000
 She felt a flush of pride at that feat,

00:44:01.000 --> 00:44:04.000
 knew that it would be a story told around the campfire this very night,

00:44:04.000 --> 00:44:07.000
 adding to the tails that were growing up around Corbin

00:44:07.000 --> 00:44:09.000
 and his wolfen companion.

00:44:09.000 --> 00:44:12.000
 The other giant lay upon his front.

00:44:12.000 --> 00:44:15.000
 Gah and Corbin tried to turn him over together,

00:44:15.000 --> 00:44:17.000
 flies buzzed angrily,

00:44:17.000 --> 00:44:20.000
 the huge warrior's dead weight like a boulder.

00:44:20.000 --> 00:44:22.000
 Ferrell and Laith joined them,

00:44:22.000 --> 00:44:24.000
 and together they rolled the giant,

00:44:24.000 --> 00:44:26.000
 the stench of corruption and decay,

00:44:26.000 --> 00:44:29.000
 wafting up to them as they disturbed the body.

00:44:29.000 --> 00:44:33.000
 "He is of the Jotun clan," Laith spat,

00:44:33.000 --> 00:44:36.000
 as they stood instead of a dead giant.

00:44:36.000 --> 00:44:39.000
 "What are they doing here?"

00:44:39.000 --> 00:44:41.000
 Corlin's eyes were drawn to the glint of leather

00:44:41.000 --> 00:44:43.000
 and iron amidst the congealed blood.

00:44:43.000 --> 00:44:46.000
 She bent and wrapped a fist around the hilt of a sword,

00:44:46.000 --> 00:44:48.000
 buried deep in the giant's thigh,

00:44:48.000 --> 00:44:50.000
 angled upwards into its groin.

00:44:50.000 --> 00:44:53.000
 He came free with a sucking sound,

00:44:53.000 --> 00:44:55.000
 and she lifted it for them all to see.

00:44:55.000 --> 00:44:58.000
 The pommel shaped like a howling wolfen.

00:44:58.000 --> 00:45:00.000
 The relief she'd felt fled,

00:45:00.000 --> 00:45:03.000
 replaced by the crushing weight of fear.

00:45:03.000 --> 00:45:07.000
 "That's band sword," Dath said, as he joined them.

00:45:07.000 --> 00:45:10.000
 Cola, a pace behind him.

00:45:10.000 --> 00:45:12.000
 Corlin stared at them a moment,

00:45:12.000 --> 00:45:14.000
 caught a wave of sympathy for them.

00:45:14.000 --> 00:45:18.000
 They'd been weighed less than two nights.

00:45:18.000 --> 00:45:21.000
 Gah took the sword from her and stared at it.

00:45:21.000 --> 00:45:24.000
 "I watched band's dar give him this blade."

00:45:24.000 --> 00:45:28.000
 "In the row and field at Dunkarig," Farrell said,

00:45:28.000 --> 00:45:30.000
 "I remember it."

00:45:30.000 --> 00:45:33.000
 "And I," Dath muttered.

00:45:33.000 --> 00:45:35.000
 Cola turned away,

00:45:35.000 --> 00:45:37.000
 her eyes scanning the ground,

00:45:37.000 --> 00:45:39.000
 searching for any sign.

00:45:39.000 --> 00:45:41.000
 "He is not here."

00:45:41.000 --> 00:45:42.000
 Storm is not here.

00:45:42.000 --> 00:45:46.000
 They escaped, but they did not make their way back to Drasil.

00:45:46.000 --> 00:45:48.000
 "Why?"

00:45:48.000 --> 00:45:51.000
 Brenner was on her knees beside the giant.

00:45:51.000 --> 00:45:53.000
 The old healer had a file in one hand,

00:45:53.000 --> 00:45:55.000
 a knife in the other that she was using to scrape blood

00:45:55.000 --> 00:45:58.000
 from the trampled grass.

00:45:58.000 --> 00:46:01.000
 One side of Brenner's face was still an angry red,

00:46:01.000 --> 00:46:03.000
 seared by the explosion she had generated

00:46:03.000 --> 00:46:07.000
 that rocked the chamber and Drasil yesterday.

00:46:07.000 --> 00:46:10.000
 Whatever benefit Brenner thought the giant's blood would bring,

00:46:10.000 --> 00:46:12.000
 she was welcome to it.

00:46:12.000 --> 00:46:15.000
 As Corlin scanned the rest of the clearing,

00:46:15.000 --> 00:46:19.000
 her eyes caught a patch of crushed grass spattered with blood.

00:46:19.000 --> 00:46:21.000
 It was close to the edge of the glade,

00:46:21.000 --> 00:46:25.000
 leading to his sheer drop to the river below.

00:46:25.000 --> 00:46:28.000
 As if something were dragged,

00:46:28.000 --> 00:46:31.000
 she followed the marks and dropped to a crouch,

00:46:31.000 --> 00:46:34.000
 looking down to the river.

00:46:34.000 --> 00:46:37.000
 Further down she spied a dark smear on a boulder.

00:46:37.000 --> 00:46:39.000
 Blood.

00:46:39.000 --> 00:46:41.000
 They jumped into the river.

00:46:41.000 --> 00:46:43.000
 She galled out.

00:46:43.000 --> 00:46:45.000
 Gar was first to join her.

00:46:45.000 --> 00:46:47.000
 His eyes found the same evidence,

00:46:47.000 --> 00:46:49.000
 and he gripped her wrist.

00:46:49.000 --> 00:46:52.000
 After them, he said.

00:46:52.000 --> 00:46:54.000
 Corlin led the way,

00:46:54.000 --> 00:46:57.000
 running along the ridge that shadowed the river,

00:46:57.000 --> 00:47:00.000
 twisting around thick-rooted trees in dense vegetation.

00:47:00.000 --> 00:47:03.000
 Her eyes flitting between the path she was navigating

00:47:03.000 --> 00:47:05.000
 and the banks of the river.

00:47:05.000 --> 00:47:08.000
 Rounding a sharp bend in the path,

00:47:08.000 --> 00:47:11.000
 she suddenly saw a shape lying on a grassy verge,

00:47:11.000 --> 00:47:14.000
 firm atted, and bloodstained.

00:47:14.000 --> 00:47:16.000
 Her heart stopped.

00:47:16.000 --> 00:47:18.000
 Storm.

00:47:18.000 --> 00:47:21.000
 She skidied to a halt on the ridge above the wolfen,

00:47:21.000 --> 00:47:25.000
 her part of her mind noticing large boot prints in the grass.

00:47:25.000 --> 00:47:27.000
 In a spray of dirt,

00:47:27.000 --> 00:47:29.000
 she scrambled over the edge,

00:47:29.000 --> 00:47:33.000
 clinging to root and vine as she made her way down to the river bank.

00:47:33.000 --> 00:47:36.000
 Storm lay still as stone,

00:47:36.000 --> 00:47:40.000
 and she was covered in blood a huge wound was visible above her shoulder.

00:47:40.000 --> 00:47:44.000
 Corlin crouched, too scared to touch her,

00:47:44.000 --> 00:47:47.000
 not wanting to confirm what her eyes were telling her.

00:47:47.000 --> 00:47:49.000
 Stifling tears,

00:47:49.000 --> 00:47:52.000
 she remembered the first time she had seen Storm,

00:47:52.000 --> 00:47:55.000
 when she had threatened to turn the wolfen into a cloak.

00:47:55.000 --> 00:47:58.000
 Even then, she had seen the bond between Corbin

00:47:58.000 --> 00:48:01.000
 and his faithful and vigilant shadow.

00:48:01.000 --> 00:48:05.000
 Since then, she had developed her own bond with the wolfen,

00:48:05.000 --> 00:48:08.000
 more like a sword brother to her than a mere animal.

00:48:08.000 --> 00:48:10.000
 As guard joined her,

00:48:10.000 --> 00:48:14.000
 she tentatively reached out her hand and laid it upon Storm's body.

00:48:14.000 --> 00:48:16.000
 She felt nothing.

00:48:16.000 --> 00:48:17.000
 No.

00:48:17.000 --> 00:48:20.000
 Please, Elion above.

00:48:20.000 --> 00:48:22.000
 She screwed her eyes shut tight,

00:48:22.000 --> 00:48:24.000
 pressed harder,

00:48:24.000 --> 00:48:27.000
 flattening her palm against Storm's deep chest,

00:48:27.000 --> 00:48:29.000
 willing her hands to feel the movement of life,

00:48:29.000 --> 00:48:32.000
 a drawn breath, the pumping of Storm's heart.

00:48:32.000 --> 00:48:35.000
 With every moment, her hopes faded,

00:48:35.000 --> 00:48:40.000
 a bleakness taking hold inside spreading through her like ink through water.

00:48:40.000 --> 00:48:43.000
 And then, she felt it.

00:48:43.000 --> 00:48:48.000
 A flicker, a heartbeat deep within the cavern of Storm's broad chest.

00:48:48.000 --> 00:48:52.000
 Corlin opened her eyes and saw Storm's amber gaze regarding her.

00:48:52.000 --> 00:48:55.000
 The wolfen whined a weak, miserable sound,

00:48:55.000 --> 00:48:58.000
 but one that gave Corlin a rush of joy.

00:48:58.000 --> 00:49:01.000
 Storm's tail thumped feebly on the turf.

00:49:01.000 --> 00:49:07.000
 Chapter 4.

00:49:07.000 --> 00:49:10.000
 Corbin

00:49:10.000 --> 00:49:12.000
 Corbin walked through a world of grey,

00:49:12.000 --> 00:49:14.000
 dimly aware that he was staggering,

00:49:14.000 --> 00:49:17.000
 close to a wide and dark river.

00:49:17.000 --> 00:49:19.000
 There was a splash and a wide ripple,

00:49:19.000 --> 00:49:23.000
 the hint of something large and sinuous in its depths.

00:49:23.000 --> 00:49:25.000
 Bloated dark clouds boiled above him,

00:49:25.000 --> 00:49:27.000
 flickering with lightning,

00:49:27.000 --> 00:49:32.000
 and black shapes winged through them with an occasional gleam of chainmail and iron.

00:49:32.000 --> 00:49:35.000
 This is the other world.

00:49:35.000 --> 00:49:41.000
 His knee throbbed and a pain spasm through his chest with every in-drawn breath.

00:49:41.000 --> 00:49:43.000
 He fixed his eyes on the ground before him,

00:49:43.000 --> 00:49:46.000
 concentrated on each step.

00:49:46.000 --> 00:49:49.000
 There had always been an element of the other world that calmed him,

00:49:49.000 --> 00:49:54.000
 a serenity that settled within him that gave him a sense of strength and hope.

00:49:54.000 --> 00:49:56.000
 But this time was different.

00:49:56.000 --> 00:49:59.000
 There was something frayed about the peacefulness.

00:49:59.000 --> 00:50:01.000
 It felt false.

00:50:01.000 --> 00:50:03.000
 Something lurked at the fringes of his mind,

00:50:03.000 --> 00:50:07.000
 trying, needing to be remembered.

00:50:07.000 --> 00:50:09.000
 When next he looked up,

00:50:09.000 --> 00:50:11.000
 the river was flowing into a valley,

00:50:11.000 --> 00:50:15.000
 cliffs rearing up by the side of him tall and forbidding.

00:50:15.000 --> 00:50:19.000
 The head of him, the river spilt into a lake.

00:50:19.000 --> 00:50:23.000
 Vibrant colour was seeping into the landscape with every step into the valley,

00:50:23.000 --> 00:50:29.000
 the grass grew greener, the river bluer, as if colour was seeping up from the rock below.

00:50:29.000 --> 00:50:31.000
 I know this place.

00:50:31.000 --> 00:50:33.000
 Have been here before.

00:50:33.000 --> 00:50:37.000
 The green valley and the lake of deep blue.

00:50:37.000 --> 00:50:40.000
 Gentle waves lapped against the shore.

00:50:40.000 --> 00:50:43.000
 A sound drew Corbin's eye towards the lake's heart,

00:50:43.000 --> 00:50:48.000
 a splash and ripples as if a stone had been thrown into water.

00:50:48.000 --> 00:50:51.000
 His memory prodded at him and his eyes wandered back to the lake shore,

00:50:51.000 --> 00:50:54.000
 searching for something else and then he saw it.

00:50:54.000 --> 00:50:59.000
 The red leafed maple that he had once sat beneath.

00:50:59.000 --> 00:51:03.000
 Without thinking he made his way to it and sat down his back to the trunk.

00:51:03.000 --> 00:51:05.000
 Everything was still.

00:51:05.000 --> 00:51:09.000
 No breeze to stir the grass or leaves, no harm of insects.

00:51:09.000 --> 00:51:12.000
 The silence was oppressive.

00:51:12.000 --> 00:51:18.000
 And then, high above, like a heartbeat, there was a beat of wings.

00:51:18.000 --> 00:51:24.000
 He glanced up through the lattice of leaf and bark and saw a figure silhouetted against the clouds,

00:51:24.000 --> 00:51:31.000
 human-like, a spear clutched in one hand, broad white feathered wings powering it through the air.

