 Rafe had the sense to dip his head as he spoke, avoiding the urge to glance at more canton's smirk.

01:25:12.000 --> 01:25:16.000
 "And I am sorry," my queen.

01:25:16.000 --> 01:25:19.000
 He added for good measure.

01:25:19.000 --> 01:25:21.000
 Ryn waved a hand.

01:25:21.000 --> 01:25:24.000
 "Sorry, there's not good enough," she said.

01:25:24.000 --> 01:25:29.000
 A tone entering her voice that scared Rafe, "I am your queen."

01:25:29.000 --> 01:25:32.000
 "And you are my subject."

01:25:32.000 --> 01:25:34.000
 "Learn your place."

01:25:34.000 --> 01:25:37.000
 "I will," Rafe muttered.

01:25:37.000 --> 01:25:40.000
 "See that you do," Ryn said.

01:25:40.000 --> 01:25:48.000
 "And also make sure that the next time I send for you you come, your life is mine."

01:25:48.000 --> 01:25:52.000
 She stared at him, no hint of expression on her face.

01:25:52.000 --> 01:25:58.000
 "Now I can make it a good life or an unpleasantly short one."

01:25:58.000 --> 01:25:59.000
 Rafe gulped.

01:25:59.000 --> 01:26:02.000
 "Do we understand one another?"

01:26:02.000 --> 01:26:05.000
 "I," my queen.

01:26:05.000 --> 01:26:06.000
 Rafe nodded.

01:26:06.000 --> 01:26:07.000
 "Good."

01:26:07.000 --> 01:26:11.000
 "Now come over here and help me with this map.

01:26:11.000 --> 01:26:19.000
 I aim to have a diner's head on a platter within a ten-night."

01:26:19.000 --> 01:26:21.000
 Chapter 6

01:26:21.000 --> 01:26:24.000
 Kamlin

01:26:24.000 --> 01:26:27.000
 Kamlin patted along the stream's edge.

01:26:27.000 --> 01:26:30.000
 His bow held loosely in one hand.

01:26:30.000 --> 01:26:33.000
 He was returning to Dunn-Krin from a hunting trip.

01:26:33.000 --> 01:26:35.000
 Hunting men.

01:26:35.000 --> 01:26:38.000
 It had been a ten-night since the battle of Dunn-Krin,

01:26:38.000 --> 01:26:42.000
 where Evanis and Morgan's war band had been largely scattered.

01:26:42.000 --> 01:26:46.000
 He and a score of others had set about hunting down the stragglers.

01:26:46.000 --> 01:26:51.000
 The more we kill now, the fewer we'll come back to try and kill us later.

01:26:51.000 --> 01:26:54.000
 Kamlin had split his hunting party into pairs,

01:26:54.000 --> 01:26:57.000
 although he himself had ended up in a group of three.

01:26:57.000 --> 01:27:03.000
 He glanced down at Meg, the band who he had rescued from a village on the outskirts of the marshlands.

01:27:03.000 --> 01:27:09.000
 Though she's more than paid me back, the time she saved my hide now.

01:27:09.000 --> 01:27:11.000
 She was walking alongside him,

01:27:11.000 --> 01:27:15.000
 wearing a warrior's leather jerkin, holding a spear in one hand,

01:27:15.000 --> 01:27:18.000
 her other resting upon the pommel of a new dagger that was hanging at her belt,

01:27:18.000 --> 01:27:22.000
 all of them spoils taken from the battle of Dunn-Krin.

01:27:22.000 --> 01:27:26.000
 Kamlin had helped her cut down and re-stitch the jerkin,

01:27:26.000 --> 01:27:31.000
 as well as chopping an arm's length of the spear to make it more manageable for her.

01:27:31.000 --> 01:27:35.000
 Part of him had been concerned about her accompanying him.

01:27:35.000 --> 01:27:37.000
 She seemed worse, though.

01:27:37.000 --> 01:27:40.000
 A memory of the mottled feet of a band swinging from gallows,

01:27:40.000 --> 01:27:46.000
 insinuated its way into his mind, beneath it bloated corpses littering a courtyard.

01:27:46.000 --> 01:27:48.000
 Much worse.

01:27:48.000 --> 01:27:50.000
 A shadow crossed his path,

01:27:50.000 --> 01:27:54.000
 and he looked up to see the third member of his party flying above him.

01:27:54.000 --> 01:27:58.000
 Craft swooped down and squorked loudly.

01:27:58.000 --> 01:28:00.000
 Dark waters?

01:28:00.000 --> 01:28:02.000
 Tall towers?

01:28:02.000 --> 01:28:04.000
 I know.

01:28:04.000 --> 01:28:06.000
 Kamlin muttered.

01:28:06.000 --> 01:28:09.000
 So I'll need a bird to tell me when I'm close to home.

01:28:09.000 --> 01:28:13.000
 Nevertheless, he raised a hand at Craft.

01:28:13.000 --> 01:28:15.000
 When I first met that bird,

01:28:15.000 --> 01:28:17.000
 I must confess I didn't like him much.

01:28:17.000 --> 01:28:21.000
 Turns out he's right-handy to have a bow, though.

01:28:21.000 --> 01:28:26.000
 Craft had led him straight to over a dozen enemy warriors lost in the marshes.

01:28:26.000 --> 01:28:29.000
 Kamlin had made sure they stayed lost,

01:28:29.000 --> 01:28:32.000
 left them lying face down in the mud.

01:28:32.000 --> 01:28:34.000
 He walked through a last bank of reeds

01:28:34.000 --> 01:28:37.000
 and came out on the shore of a huge lake.

01:28:37.000 --> 01:28:41.000
 The towers and walls of Duncan reared out of the lake's waters,

01:28:41.000 --> 01:28:46.000
 damp and moss-covered like some frozen Leviathan.

01:28:46.000 --> 01:28:51.000
 Figures moved on the battleman walls, boats scuddling between towers.

01:28:51.000 --> 01:28:54.000
 All about him on the lake sure there was motion.

01:28:54.000 --> 01:28:59.000
 The wives and bands of the warriors who had fought in the battle of Duncan had finally returned

01:28:59.000 --> 01:29:01.000
 from their hiding place deeper in the marshes,

01:29:01.000 --> 01:29:04.000
 and all manner of rough shelters were being erected,

01:29:04.000 --> 01:29:10.000
 mostly consisting of linen tents and panelled walls of woven willow.

01:29:10.000 --> 01:29:14.000
 Best not make themselves too comfortable.

01:29:14.000 --> 01:29:18.000
 Meg dashed off and merged into the crowds.

01:29:18.000 --> 01:29:22.000
 Kamlin watched as a pair of children rummaged amongst the piles of war gear

01:29:22.000 --> 01:29:26.000
 that have been stripped from the dead and heaped in mounds along the lake sure.

01:29:26.000 --> 01:29:32.000
 Great stacks of swords and spears, shields, boots, belts, knives, quivers,

01:29:32.000 --> 01:29:38.000
 shirts of mail, courasses of boiled leather and cloaks of black and gold.

01:29:38.000 --> 01:29:41.000
 Meg reappeared at his side.

01:29:41.000 --> 01:29:45.000
 Now with an iron helmet much too big for her head added to her outfit.

01:29:45.000 --> 01:29:49.000
 Kamlin tried not to laugh but wasn't wholly successful.

01:29:49.000 --> 01:29:50.000
 What?

01:29:50.000 --> 01:29:52.000
 Meg scalded him.

01:29:52.000 --> 01:29:56.000
 "Think that helmet might slow you down?" he said.

01:29:56.000 --> 01:29:59.000
 "Besides, your head's thick enough.

01:29:59.000 --> 01:30:01.000
 Doubt if you'll need it."

01:30:01.000 --> 01:30:03.000
 She punched him in the leg.

01:30:03.000 --> 01:30:05.000
 "When are we leaving?" she asked.

01:30:05.000 --> 01:30:08.000
 "Don't know." he shrugged.

01:30:08.000 --> 01:30:12.000
 Probably talk about it a while before we get around to doing this.

01:30:12.000 --> 01:30:16.000
 He paused as the crowds opened up before him.

01:30:16.000 --> 01:30:20.000
 Yidana was walking calmly through their midst, stopping down again to address

01:30:20.000 --> 01:30:24.000
 someone directly, holding a hand here, cupping a cheek there,

01:30:24.000 --> 01:30:28.000
 always seeming to be interested in what was being said to her.

01:30:28.000 --> 01:30:34.000
 Baird, the one-eyed warrior of Darwin, and Von, accompanied her.

01:30:34.000 --> 01:30:39.000
 Kamlin frowned as he watched the young warrior, his eye shadowed with dark circles, grief,

01:30:39.000 --> 01:30:42.000
 carving new lines upon his face.

01:30:42.000 --> 01:30:45.000
 "No, I'd guess I'm partly to blame for that."

01:30:45.000 --> 01:30:49.000
 Me having killed his dar might have something to do with his current mood.

01:30:49.000 --> 01:30:55.000
 He tracked Von after the battle, found him leagues from anywhere, alone apart from his dar.

01:30:55.000 --> 01:30:57.000
 Everness.

01:30:57.000 --> 01:31:00.000
 Kamlin had watched as they'd argued.

01:31:00.000 --> 01:31:04.000
 He'd had ended with Von turning his back on Everness and walking away.

01:31:04.000 --> 01:31:10.000
 Everness had followed, hand dipping inside his cloaking, coming out with a knife for his fist.

01:31:10.000 --> 01:31:14.000
 Kamlin had put two arrows through the man's chest.

01:31:14.000 --> 01:31:18.000
 His eyes flicked back to Adana.

01:31:18.000 --> 01:31:23.000
 She has grown since that night in Dunkari, when she saw her dar murdered.

01:31:23.000 --> 01:31:28.000
 Even fought Roshin of Darwin in the court of swords and one.

01:31:28.000 --> 01:31:32.000
 Mind, exile was too good for a woman like that.

01:31:32.000 --> 01:31:35.000
 She'll never stop her trouble-making.

01:31:35.000 --> 01:31:40.000
 He searched behind Adana, looking for his friend, Halion.

01:31:40.000 --> 01:31:42.000
 He should be back by now.

01:31:42.000 --> 01:31:48.000
 Then he saw him sitting beside a fire with Lorcan, Halion's half-brother, Roshin's son,

01:31:48.000 --> 01:31:53.000
 heir to the throne of Darwin, and unofficially betrothed at Adana, with his shieldman,

01:31:53.000 --> 01:31:57.000
 broken no-neck as Meg affectionately referred to him.

01:31:57.000 --> 01:32:00.000
 "Good to see you," Halion said.

01:32:00.000 --> 01:32:03.000
 Rising and gripping Kamlin's forearm.

01:32:03.000 --> 01:32:07.000
 "You too," Kamlin said with a grin.

01:32:07.000 --> 01:32:13.000
 Kamlin looked at their faces, saw they were all somber, attention in the air.

01:32:13.000 --> 01:32:17.000
 Lorcan's dark eyes were red, looked as if he'd been weeping.

01:32:17.000 --> 01:32:20.000
 "Am I into Robson?" Kamlin asked.

01:32:20.000 --> 01:32:23.000
 "Just tell me to bugger off if I am."

01:32:23.000 --> 01:32:28.000
 "No, Kamlin," Lorcan said, standing and surreptitiously wiping his eyes.

01:32:28.000 --> 01:32:31.000
 Like it was just going.

01:32:31.000 --> 01:32:36.000
 He bathe him farewell, Halion squeezing his shoulder and left.

01:32:36.000 --> 01:32:39.000
 Brogan followed faithfully in his wake.

01:32:39.000 --> 01:32:42.000
 "He are eight," Kamlin asked.

01:32:42.000 --> 01:32:45.000
 "No," Halion said honestly.

01:32:45.000 --> 01:32:48.000
 "But I think he will be."

01:32:48.000 --> 01:32:51.000
 I know Connell hates him just for being Russian son, but I like him.

01:32:51.000 --> 01:32:53.000
 There's no malice in him.

01:32:53.000 --> 01:32:57.000
 "Well, that's a rare thing," Kamlin observed.

01:32:57.000 --> 01:33:01.000
 And he did the right thing with Russian.

01:33:01.000 --> 01:33:04.000
 Choosing Adana over his mum wasn't easy.

01:33:04.000 --> 01:33:06.000
 "True," Kamlin said.

01:33:06.000 --> 01:33:09.000
 "Some times that I think could be a grim thing too."

01:33:09.000 --> 01:33:15.000
 "I, and it's weighing heavy on him, and you, by the look of it."

01:33:15.000 --> 01:33:19.000
 Halion looked tired, a strained look about his eyes.

01:33:19.000 --> 01:33:21.000
 Chopped on, then.

01:33:21.000 --> 01:33:23.000
 Kamlin asked Halion.

01:33:23.000 --> 01:33:25.000
 "Hi," Halion breathed.

01:33:25.000 --> 01:33:27.000
 Got back yesterday.

01:33:27.000 --> 01:33:29.000
 Did it go?"

01:33:29.000 --> 01:33:33.000
 He was going to say well, but that didn't seem like the right word.

01:33:33.000 --> 01:33:36.000
 Halion looked away, staring out into the marshland.

01:33:36.000 --> 01:33:39.000
 "Rushing didn't try to escape, if that's what you mean."

01:33:39.000 --> 01:33:42.000
 "That's something," Kamlin said.

01:33:42.000 --> 01:33:44.000
 "I," Halion shrugged.

01:33:44.000 --> 01:33:47.000
 "Not the easiest thing I've done," he added.

01:33:47.000 --> 01:33:49.000
 As Kamlin continued to stare at him.

01:33:49.000 --> 01:33:51.000
 "Thought you hated Russian."

01:33:51.000 --> 01:33:52.000
 "I do."

01:33:52.000 --> 01:33:57.000
 She murdered my mum, wanted to kill me, and Connell was the reason we fled down.

01:33:57.000 --> 01:33:59.000
 And she would have murdered Adana too.

01:33:59.000 --> 01:34:02.000
 Exile is better than she deserves.

01:34:02.000 --> 01:34:05.000
 "But," Halion shrugged.

01:34:05.000 --> 01:34:09.000
 His sea gray eyes hinting at the emotion he kept buried within.

01:34:09.000 --> 01:34:11.000
 Walking away was hard.

01:34:11.000 --> 01:34:14.000
 Execution is hard, you mean.

01:34:14.000 --> 01:34:17.000
 We called it exile, but leaving her in the middle of the marsh.

01:34:17.000 --> 01:34:19.000
 It was a death sentence.

01:34:19.000 --> 01:34:22.000
 Kamlin patted, Halion shoulder.

01:34:22.000 --> 01:34:24.000
 Good hunting?"

01:34:24.000 --> 01:34:26.000
 Halion asked him.

01:34:26.000 --> 01:34:27.000
 "I."

01:34:27.000 --> 01:34:31.000
 There are few less warriors in black and gold to tell the way to this place.

01:34:31.000 --> 01:34:34.000
 "Am I the fair's back?"

01:34:34.000 --> 01:34:37.000
 "No, you're the last," Halion said.

01:34:37.000 --> 01:34:39.000
 "But we'll be waiting on you."

01:34:39.000 --> 01:34:43.000
 Adana refused to hold the council until you were back safe and sound.

01:34:43.000 --> 01:34:47.000
 Kamlin felt himself blush at that, a smile, twitching his lips.

01:34:47.000 --> 01:34:51.000
 It felt strange to be valued.

01:34:51.000 --> 01:34:54.000
 Kamlin looked around the circle of familiar faces.

01:34:54.000 --> 01:34:58.000
 They were gathered in a clearing, amidst the ruins of what looked

01:34:58.000 --> 01:35:01.000
 to have once been done Cron's gatehouse.

01:35:01.000 --> 01:35:07.000
 A collapsed tower arose above them, birds nests poking from its crumbled ramparts.

01:35:07.000 --> 01:35:12.000
 The old wall lay in ruins, granite boulders scattered in the grass.

01:35:12.000 --> 01:35:19.000
 Beneath their feet, ancient flagstones lay twisted and shattered by the encroaching roots of willow and older.

01:35:19.000 --> 01:35:25.000
 A crumbling archway framed Adana, who sat upon a moss-covered boulder.

01:35:25.000 --> 01:35:33.000
 She looked at home in a coat of mail and boiled leather circles, a great cloak about her shoulders and a sword at her hip.

01:35:33.000 --> 01:35:36.000
 Surrounding her were though she trusted most closely.

01:35:36.000 --> 01:35:39.000
 Pindathrin, her barrel-chested uncle.

01:35:39.000 --> 01:35:46.000
 And trust, the red-haired warrior from Navon once shielded to Owen, Navon's fallen king.

01:35:46.000 --> 01:35:52.000
 Lornkin, the young king in exile of Darwin, gaze solemnly at Adana.

01:35:52.000 --> 01:35:57.000
 The others that filled the area were mostly warriors, shieldmen to those present.

01:35:57.000 --> 01:36:01.000
 Halion, von, and one-eyed bed, watching Adana.

01:36:01.000 --> 01:36:06.000
 Close to them, broken, loomed, protectively close to Lornkin.

01:36:06.000 --> 01:36:11.000
 Craft perched upon the broken archway above Adana like a carved statue.

01:36:11.000 --> 01:36:15.000
 And I've no doubt that Meg is eavesdropping somewhere close by.

01:36:15.000 --> 01:36:21.000
 Adana stood, and the quiet conversations that had whispered amongst the ruined walls hushed.

01:36:21.000 --> 01:36:26.000
 "We are leaving down Kryn," she said, without any preamble.

01:36:26.000 --> 01:36:29.000
 Above her, Craft ruffled his feathers.

01:36:29.000 --> 01:36:32.000
 Leaving, he caught quietly.

01:36:32.000 --> 01:36:36.000
 "Our warriors' kin have only just returned," trust objected.

01:36:36.000 --> 01:36:38.000
 Not even dried their feet.

01:36:38.000 --> 01:36:41.000
 And this is a good defensible spot.

01:36:41.000 --> 01:36:44.000
 There were rumbles of ascent.

01:36:44.000 --> 01:36:48.000
 After our victory they don't want to leave, I've seen it before.

01:36:48.000 --> 01:36:51.000
 The victory makes them feel secure.

01:36:51.000 --> 01:36:54.000
 But our enemies know full, rins as canny as they come.

01:36:54.000 --> 01:36:56.000
 We'll not defeat her here again.

01:36:56.000 --> 01:36:59.000
 And he had said as much to Adana.

01:36:59.000 --> 01:37:01.000
 "I agree," Adana said.

01:37:01.000 --> 01:37:03.000
 "We won the last skirmish."

01:37:03.000 --> 01:37:07.000
 Ryn and her battle chiefs underestimated us, and did not scout well enough.

01:37:07.000 --> 01:37:12.000
 But they will not repeat that mistake, and they will be back.

01:37:12.000 --> 01:37:20.000
 We faced over 500 swords, put more than 300 in their cans, but however many we slew some escaped.

01:37:20.000 --> 01:37:24.000
 They know where we are, and they will report back to Ryn.

01:37:24.000 --> 01:37:29.000
 Next time they will be cautious, and Ryn rules four realms now.

01:37:29.000 --> 01:37:33.000
 She has the numbers to keep throwing warriors at us until we are overwhelmed.

01:37:33.000 --> 01:37:36.000
 And after in nodded Dowley in agreement.

01:37:36.000 --> 01:37:39.000
 But where else is there?

01:37:39.000 --> 01:37:44.000
 There are one or two other spots in these marshes, just said.

01:37:44.000 --> 01:37:47.000
 Not as good as here, but still.

01:37:47.000 --> 01:37:51.000
 We need to change our tactics.

01:37:51.000 --> 01:37:55.000
 Only the families are staying in the marshes, you're done or interrupted.

01:37:55.000 --> 01:37:58.000
 Now I'm leading the warband out into Arden.

01:37:58.000 --> 01:38:02.000
 Arden, Kraftmotted above Adana.

01:38:02.000 --> 01:38:06.000
 He didn't look pleased, the feathers of his neck suddenly bristling.

01:38:06.000 --> 01:38:07.000
 What?

01:38:07.000 --> 01:38:09.000
 Pindaphragm blurted.

01:38:09.000 --> 01:38:10.000
 Now that is.

01:38:10.000 --> 01:38:16.000
 He paused face turning redder as he made an obvious effort to master his tongue.

01:38:16.000 --> 01:38:17.000
 But why?

01:38:17.000 --> 01:38:22.000
 We cannot win the war, hiding in these marshes.

01:38:22.000 --> 01:38:30.000
 If Ryn is to be defeated, and Arden, Narvan and Dowan set free, then we must take the battle to her.

01:38:30.000 --> 01:38:35.000
 We must become an enemy she fears.

01:38:35.000 --> 01:38:38.000
 Winning one battle does not decide the war, dress said.

01:38:38.000 --> 01:38:43.000
 You've done well, but we could lead Ryn a merry dance around these marshes.

01:38:43.000 --> 01:38:46.000
 I know full well that the war is not one.

01:38:46.000 --> 01:38:49.000
 Adana said, her voice abruptly cold.

01:38:49.000 --> 01:38:51.000
 Do not patronise me.

01:38:51.000 --> 01:38:56.000
 I am not a ban, and I am no stranger to loss and hardship.

01:38:56.000 --> 01:38:58.000
 She looks around at them all.

01:38:58.000 --> 01:39:00.000
 Each night I close my eyes.

01:39:00.000 --> 01:39:03.000
 Each day I awake I see the same thing.

01:39:03.000 --> 01:39:09.000
 My dead kin, my friends cut down my home, burning my people.

01:39:09.000 --> 01:39:13.000
 Who cares for them while we are here?

01:39:13.000 --> 01:39:16.000
 Never forget what Ryn has taken from us.

01:39:16.000 --> 01:39:19.000
 It is time we took something back.

01:39:19.000 --> 01:39:22.000
 Time we took the battle to her.

01:39:22.000 --> 01:39:24.000
 Just snorted.

01:39:24.000 --> 01:39:27.000
 We cannot face Ryn in open battle.

01:39:27.000 --> 01:39:29.000
 Pindaphragm growled.

01:39:29.000 --> 01:39:31.000
 Of course not, Adana said.

01:39:31.000 --> 01:39:37.000
 We are to few in numbers, less than 200 swords, but we can use that to our advantage.

01:39:37.000 --> 01:39:42.000
 We can move quickly, strike fast, disappear, strike elsewhere.

01:39:42.000 --> 01:39:46.000
 Show Ryn and the people of Arden that we have teeth.

01:39:46.000 --> 01:39:50.000
 Pindaphragm nodded, obviously considering it.

01:39:50.000 --> 01:39:53.000
 "That lonely last so long," he said.

01:39:53.000 --> 01:39:56.000
 Indeed, Adana said.

01:39:56.000 --> 01:40:00.000
 Which is why the word needs the spread that Ryn has lost a great battle that her

01:40:00.000 --> 01:40:02.000
 regent evidence is dead.

01:40:02.000 --> 01:40:06.000
 Her eyes flitted to Von and she took a deep breath.

01:40:06.000 --> 01:40:10.000
 "That the rightful queen of Arden has returned.

01:40:10.000 --> 01:40:12.000
 The people need to know.

01:40:12.000 --> 01:40:14.000
 They have not been forgotten.

01:40:14.000 --> 01:40:15.000
 I know them.

01:40:15.000 --> 01:40:19.000
 They will join us if we offer them hope."

01:40:19.000 --> 01:40:21.000
 Pindaphragm glanced at Rost.

01:40:21.000 --> 01:40:25.000
 They shared alongside us than Rost nodded grimly.

01:40:25.000 --> 01:40:31.000
 "When did the girly I used to bounce upon my knee become this daring battle chief I see before me?"

01:40:31.000 --> 01:40:33.000
 Pindaphragm said.

01:40:33.000 --> 01:40:35.000
 Adana just smiled.

01:40:35.000 --> 01:40:43.000
 Though her eyes flicked in acknowledgement to Kamlin and Halion, who had had long conversations with her, discussing the options.

01:40:43.000 --> 01:40:47.000
 Though to be fair, much of this plan came from her.

01:40:47.000 --> 01:40:53.000
 There was a flapping of wings and craft glided down to a light on the rock beside Adana.

01:40:53.000 --> 01:40:56.000
 "Drassil?" he croaked.

