 "Crouch on the far south of the camp, he saw a few dozen enemy guards standing with their

02:52:29.020 --> 02:52:34.840
 backs to him in an open space cleared between the camp and the tree-line. They looked

02:52:34.840 --> 02:52:41.820
 unsure of what to do. The man beside Makin gripped his sword and took a step forwards.

02:52:41.820 --> 02:52:49.660
 "Wait," Makin whispered, seizing the warrior's arm. "Not till Crellus hits the camp."

02:52:49.660 --> 02:52:55.420
 Makin had been given the command of a hundred men, and they were spread loosely around

02:52:55.420 --> 02:53:01.180
 him, hidden in the shadows and foliage. Only one thing had he said to them before they

02:53:01.180 --> 02:53:07.700
 had moved into position. "When I go, keep with me."

02:53:07.700 --> 02:53:11.740
 Their task was to attack from the south and sweep up through the camp, spreading

02:53:11.740 --> 02:53:15.740
 as much mayhem and panic along the way as was possible.

02:53:15.740 --> 02:53:18.740
 Makin was unused to leading men.

02:53:18.740 --> 02:53:22.620
 They've enthaled and fighting pits had honed his will to survive, teaching him that above

02:53:22.620 --> 02:53:26.180
 all else you fight for yourself.

02:53:26.180 --> 02:53:31.300
 But that is what Lycus wanted, to break me, to strip away my loyalties to make me less

02:53:31.300 --> 02:53:35.820
 than human. I will not be that man again."

02:53:35.820 --> 02:53:40.340
 The main attack was to be led by Crellus, his first objective to clear the new road of

02:53:40.340 --> 02:53:45.180
 all resistance. He was there that their scouts had reported most of Gundles' warband were

02:53:45.180 --> 02:53:47.380
 to be found.

02:53:47.380 --> 02:53:52.180
 Once the road was clear, Crellus was to assault the camp, which was the signal for the

02:53:52.180 --> 02:53:53.180
 others.

02:53:53.180 --> 02:53:58.340
 Makin and Albin were leading smaller groups hidden to the west and south of the camp.

02:53:58.340 --> 02:54:03.220
 The plan was to meet Crellus and his force at the command tent, situated on a hill

02:54:03.220 --> 02:54:05.340
 close to the camp centre.

02:54:05.340 --> 02:54:10.980
 At the thought of it, begins our eyes drifted to the tent on the mound.

02:54:10.980 --> 02:54:14.620
 Men were appearing from its entrance, standing and staring at the commotion that Crellus

02:54:14.620 --> 02:54:15.620
 was causing.

02:54:15.620 --> 02:54:19.500
 Gundles. It must be.

02:54:19.500 --> 02:54:26.300
 Two other men emerged from the tent, hanging back from the rest. One of them seemed familiar

02:54:26.300 --> 02:54:30.660
 in the way he walked, his posture, a confidence.

02:54:30.660 --> 02:54:35.100
 Then dark cloth figures were appearing from around the hill, drawing tight about those who

02:54:35.100 --> 02:54:40.540
 were to merge from the tent. Even from this distance, there was something clearly different

02:54:40.540 --> 02:54:42.580
 about them.

02:54:42.580 --> 02:54:49.940
 Kalashim. Dammit. We're outnumbered as it is without those hells spawned to complicate things.

02:54:49.940 --> 02:54:55.940
 He shrugged it himself, knew they were committed now and there was no turning back.

02:54:55.940 --> 02:55:00.100
 And this whole attack was my idea, so I'd best be getting to that tent and making sure

02:55:00.100 --> 02:55:02.900
 we win this thing.

02:55:02.900 --> 02:55:06.820
 He looked back to the road and saw Crellus' warriors pouring down the embankment and

02:55:06.820 --> 02:55:08.500
 into the camp.

02:55:08.500 --> 02:55:10.220
 Good.

02:55:10.220 --> 02:55:14.820
 With a battle cry, Hicks exploded into motion, bursting from the tree-line, drawing a knife

02:55:14.820 --> 02:55:19.860
 in each hand as he sped towards the guard, spread between him and the camp.

02:55:19.860 --> 02:55:23.820
 A few paces behind him, his hundred followed.

02:55:23.820 --> 02:55:27.940
 He heard a distant roar from the west, knew that Albon and his warriors were doing the

02:55:27.940 --> 02:55:29.540
 same.

02:55:29.540 --> 02:55:34.500
 Makim ducked a spear thrust and crashed into the man holding it, one of his knives punching

02:55:34.500 --> 02:55:39.300
 through leather into flesh, ripping it free as his momentum carried him on, leaving the man

02:55:39.300 --> 02:55:42.900
 on his knees, hands clutching at his belly.

02:55:42.900 --> 02:55:47.660
 In moments, the guards along the camp's edge were either dead or fleeing. The sudden

02:55:47.660 --> 02:55:51.540
 onslaught of Makim and his warriors too much for them.

02:55:51.540 --> 02:55:56.660
 Makim gathered his warriors in charge into the camp, kicking at fires, smashing gates open,

02:55:56.660 --> 02:56:01.820
 freeing cattle, hacking and slashing at anyone who got in their way.

02:56:01.820 --> 02:56:06.580
 In heartbeats, flames were licking at tents and smoke was billowing.

02:56:06.580 --> 02:56:12.220
 Stampedeing cattle knocked men flying, the whole world seemed to dissolve into chaos.

02:56:12.220 --> 02:56:16.860
 Makim turned a corner and almost ran into a dozen warriors, the ensuing combat savage

02:56:16.860 --> 02:56:18.060
 and short.

02:56:18.060 --> 02:56:22.700
 Makim's knives finding throats and arteries as he slipped through them like a violent wind,

02:56:22.700 --> 02:56:27.020
 the men following him crashing upon those still standing.

02:56:27.020 --> 02:56:32.140
 He sped through the camp, a knife dripping blood in each hand, leaving a trail of bodies

02:56:32.140 --> 02:56:34.220
 in his wake.

02:56:34.220 --> 02:56:39.180
 As he traveled deeper, any kind of resistance melted away, those he came across ran from

02:56:39.180 --> 02:56:41.940
 him and he was happy to let them go.

02:56:41.940 --> 02:56:48.500
 For the most part, they were not gungal's warriors, but merchants, smiths, tanners, cobblers,

02:56:48.500 --> 02:56:55.380
 whores and bands, and maybe a killer, but I'll not slay the innocent.

02:56:55.380 --> 02:57:00.820
 Soon, the initial red mist of battle began to fade, and he glanced behind, saw the black

02:57:00.820 --> 02:57:04.700
 and silver of Ripper's warriors following him.

02:57:04.700 --> 02:57:09.820
 Not used to leading men these days all being in a fight this big, mustn't forget they're

02:57:09.820 --> 02:57:13.620
 with me, mustn't forget the plan.

02:57:13.620 --> 02:57:19.020
 Pulsing, he gave his men a chance to gather behind him as he tried to get his bearings.

02:57:19.020 --> 02:57:24.420
 Screams and the concussive clash of iron drifted down from the north.

02:57:24.420 --> 02:57:25.420
 Crellis sounds closer.

02:57:25.420 --> 02:57:28.060
 Let's get to that command tent.

02:57:28.060 --> 02:57:33.140
 Gondol must die for this to succeed, and to do that, we must carve away through his

02:57:33.140 --> 02:57:35.620
 kadoshim.

02:57:35.620 --> 02:57:40.260
 He reached up to his shoulder and felt the hilt of a short sword, one of the pairs strapped

02:57:40.260 --> 02:57:42.380
 across his back.

02:57:42.380 --> 02:57:47.820
 He'd preferred using his knives, but taking heads from kadoshim was swordwork.

02:57:47.820 --> 02:57:49.900
 He set off again.

02:57:49.900 --> 02:57:54.460
 Close packed tent suddenly gave way to an open space, Cookfire spread about it, tents

02:57:54.460 --> 02:57:57.140
 forming a loose circle.

02:57:57.140 --> 02:57:59.260
 Weapons racks were rolled along one edge.

02:57:59.260 --> 02:58:05.300
 A mass of men were pulling spears from stands, strapping on helms, hefting shields.

02:58:05.300 --> 02:58:10.100
 Meking skidded to a halt, realising what he had stumbled upon.

02:58:10.100 --> 02:58:13.780
 A barracks for the warriors of this warband.

02:58:13.780 --> 02:58:16.660
 With a snail, he ran at them.

02:58:16.660 --> 02:58:21.020
 He hit a knot of men before they had any time to react, his knives tracing a red ruin

02:58:21.020 --> 02:58:23.260
 across their bodies.

02:58:23.260 --> 02:58:28.060
 In moments, he was through them and hurling himself at a new wall of men.

02:58:28.060 --> 02:58:31.180
 Weapons trusted him, but the battle rage was upon him.

02:58:31.180 --> 02:58:35.620
 The world seeming to slow, and he twisted and flowed around every blow aimed at him,

02:58:35.620 --> 02:58:40.780
 his knives licking out to slice throats, puncture groins, cut hamstrings.

02:58:40.780 --> 02:58:47.700
 Dimley, he heard the clash of arms behind him, knew his men were following.

02:58:47.700 --> 02:58:54.860
 Faces appeared before him grim, fearful, shocked, all fell to his twin blades.

02:58:54.860 --> 02:58:57.140
 His progress slowed.

02:58:57.140 --> 02:59:02.540
 The men crammed together now, his ability to move and sway hindered by a crush of bodies.

02:59:02.540 --> 02:59:08.020
 A quick glance showed his men behind him, fighting furiously, but they were outnumbered and

02:59:08.020 --> 02:59:10.820
 the enemy was beginning to curl around their flanks.

02:59:10.820 --> 02:59:16.860
 Surprise and savagery had taken them so far, but had not broken their foe.

02:59:16.860 --> 02:59:19.180
 Things are about to get messy.

02:59:19.180 --> 02:59:23.740
 Meking stepped to the right, deflected a thrust aimed at the ribs of one of his men,

02:59:23.740 --> 02:59:28.260
 slashed across the face of the attacker, kicked another in the knee, saw him buckle and stepped

02:59:28.260 --> 02:59:31.260
 close to cut his throat.

02:59:31.260 --> 02:59:36.900
 There was a great crash, and a concussion that undulated through the hard-pressed warriors.

02:59:36.900 --> 02:59:40.540
 Someone else joining this party.

02:59:40.540 --> 02:59:46.460
 Meking glimpsed a giant figure, Alcyon, wielding two Woodman's axes, as Meking was

02:59:46.460 --> 02:59:52.100
 using his knives, carving away through the enemy like a sigh that harvest time.

02:59:52.100 --> 02:59:56.740
 Heads and limbs flew through the air in great gouts of blood.

02:59:56.740 --> 02:59:58.500
 Albin's crew.

02:59:58.500 --> 03:00:03.940
 Meking grinned, and leapt at his enemy, new strength powering his muscles.

03:00:03.940 --> 03:00:07.620
 Within moments Gungal's warriors were wavering, a ripple of doubt and fear spreading

03:00:07.620 --> 03:00:10.860
 through them, and then they were fleeing.

03:00:10.860 --> 03:00:14.900
 Meking buried a knife in a back, ripped it free, and stood over the collapsing figure,

03:00:14.900 --> 03:00:17.980
 Gore covered, and breathing heavily.

03:00:17.980 --> 03:00:22.900
 He saw Alcyon decapitate one more fleeing warrior, his wife, Rayna, and their son, Tane,

03:00:22.900 --> 03:00:26.620
 either side of him, Albin's warriors spread about them.

03:00:26.620 --> 03:00:33.020
 And well met, a voice said, and Meking turned to see Albin striding towards him.

03:00:33.020 --> 03:00:37.140
 The old man was pale, and had blood seeping from the bandage around his shoulder.

03:00:37.140 --> 03:00:40.620
 I told him to stay at our camp.

03:00:40.620 --> 03:00:43.820
 He had been better off there, and I'd have been happier knowing someone of his skill

03:00:43.820 --> 03:00:46.460
 was guarding fiddily.

03:00:46.460 --> 03:00:50.860
 He felt away the fear for her as he did every time that he was parted from her, but this

03:00:50.860 --> 03:00:51.860
 was war.

03:00:51.860 --> 03:00:56.460
 They both knew that she could not be here in the midst of this.

03:00:56.460 --> 03:01:02.740
 Almette, Meking replied, "Sheathing a knife and gripping the old man's arm."

03:01:02.740 --> 03:01:09.100
 He left blood-stained fingerprints, "Think you might have just saved my skin."

03:01:09.100 --> 03:01:13.460
 Albin looked around at the body's piled about Meking and threw out the barrack ground.

03:01:13.460 --> 03:01:16.900
 "I doubt that," he said.

03:01:16.900 --> 03:01:20.860
 He glanced up through the rolling smoke at the hill that loomed not far away.

03:01:20.860 --> 03:01:23.300
 "Gundle," Meking said.

03:01:23.300 --> 03:01:26.660
 "I, let's go and find him."

03:01:26.660 --> 03:01:28.860
 Both of their war bands were about them now.

03:01:28.860 --> 03:01:32.660
 "There's Khadashim on that hill," Meking said loudly.

03:01:32.660 --> 03:01:37.060
 "They don't die easily, remember, you must take their heads."

03:01:37.060 --> 03:01:40.420
 Albin and others nodded grimly.

03:01:40.420 --> 03:01:45.500
 Meking grinned at them, then ran for the hill.

03:01:45.500 --> 03:01:49.900
 Clouds of smoke billowed about him, parted for a moment, and he saw the hill, the huge

03:01:49.900 --> 03:01:55.540
 and gordy tent upon it, strangely out of place in the somber gloom of fawn.

03:01:55.540 --> 03:01:57.180
 Meking ran faster.

03:01:57.180 --> 03:02:02.380
 The camp, a place of flame and shadow, the thud of his comrades, feet behind him, screams

03:02:02.380 --> 03:02:05.540
 and battle cries swirling on the edying smoke.

03:02:05.540 --> 03:02:09.220
 Then the ground began to rise, and he burst from the haze and tents.

03:02:09.220 --> 03:02:14.340
 Albin, Alcyon, and their men only a few paces behind him.

03:02:14.340 --> 03:02:18.420
 Men were still on the hill, but they were retreating, at least three score of the Khadashim

03:02:18.420 --> 03:02:22.540
 that encircled them were herding them north-east towards the newest part of the road.

03:02:22.540 --> 03:02:28.380
 They're fleeing, running for Jassel, and further along the road there'll be more reinforcements

03:02:28.380 --> 03:02:31.940
 can't let them reach that road.

03:02:31.940 --> 03:02:37.580
 Meking sheathed his knives and drew the two short swords as he ran.

03:02:37.580 --> 03:02:40.620
 The space between them narrowed quickly.

03:02:40.620 --> 03:02:45.100
 Meking and those with him were silent, no battle cries, only the drum of their feet and

03:02:45.100 --> 03:02:48.700
 a jangle and creek of male and leather.

03:02:48.700 --> 03:02:54.260
 Now properly, gondle and Khadashim were aware of them, gondle yelling orders.

03:02:54.260 --> 03:02:58.500
 A score of the Khadashim peeled away from the group, curved swords being drawn from behind

03:02:58.500 --> 03:03:00.700
 their backs.

03:03:00.700 --> 03:03:08.380
 One fixed its black eyes on Meking and ran at him, a dark grin splitting its pallid face.

03:03:08.380 --> 03:03:12.180
 Meking felt a fist of fear squirming his belly, remembering their ferocity and other

03:03:12.180 --> 03:03:15.660
 worldliness when he'd encountered them previously.

03:03:15.660 --> 03:03:19.740
 He growled in anger at his own fear and ran faster.

03:03:19.740 --> 03:03:24.660
 The first Khadashim almost took his head, its sword whistling her fingers with above him as

03:03:24.660 --> 03:03:29.700
 he threw himself into a roll, coming to his feet behind the creature, his own strike at its

03:03:29.700 --> 03:03:34.300
 neck blocked with blinding speed, his second blade slicing through the back of its leg

03:03:34.300 --> 03:03:37.100
 as it spun to face him.

03:03:37.100 --> 03:03:38.620
 Meking leapt away.

03:03:38.620 --> 03:03:42.980
 The creature stumbling as he tried to follow, its hamstrings cut.

03:03:42.980 --> 03:03:47.940
 Even so, it was unnaturally fast, lurching after him.

03:03:47.940 --> 03:03:52.780
 It should be on the ground, not still trying to gut me.

03:03:52.780 --> 03:03:57.660
 All around him, his warriors were locked in combat with the Khadashim, battle cries and

03:03:57.660 --> 03:03:59.740
 death screams rang out.

03:03:59.740 --> 03:04:05.500
 He glimpsed albin take a head, saw that terrible black vapor fill the air.

03:04:05.500 --> 03:04:09.620
 His distraction nearly cosmic in his life as his attacker launched a combination of two-handed

03:04:09.620 --> 03:04:11.300
 blows at him.

03:04:11.300 --> 03:04:17.500
 He parried two and slipped inside the third, instantively punching a shortsword into its belly.

03:04:17.500 --> 03:04:23.300
 The Khadashim's mouth gaped wide, foul breath washing over him as his teeth snapped, trying

03:04:23.300 --> 03:04:25.420
 to fasten on his throat.

03:04:25.420 --> 03:04:30.180
 He headbutted it, pushed away, leaving one sword in its belly, his other blade whistling

03:04:30.180 --> 03:04:35.380
 around to crunch into its collarbone, blood and bone spraying as he wrenched it free and

03:04:35.380 --> 03:04:40.180
 hacked again, this time cutting deep into the creature's neck.

03:04:40.180 --> 03:04:45.420
 He darted in, swerving away from its curved sword, chopping at its neck to finish the

03:04:45.420 --> 03:04:47.140
 job.

03:04:47.140 --> 03:04:51.220
 Somehow the Khadashim's hand snaked out and caught his blade in its fist.

03:04:51.220 --> 03:04:56.100
 A finger flew through the air but still, it held on, as it tried to bring its own sword

03:04:56.100 --> 03:04:58.460
 round to bear.

03:04:58.460 --> 03:05:02.460
 The king grabbed its sword wrist, and for a few heartbeats, they lurched together in an

03:05:02.460 --> 03:05:04.740
 ungainly dance.

03:05:04.740 --> 03:05:08.760
 Within seconds became new, he could not win a contest of strength, the Khadashim's grip was

03:05:08.760 --> 03:05:10.900
 unnaturally strong.

03:05:10.900 --> 03:05:16.100
 Then, in the blink of an eye, its head was spinning through the air and Albin's face appeared

03:05:16.100 --> 03:05:17.980
 before him.

03:05:17.980 --> 03:05:23.140
 The Khadashim's body slumped, fist still gripped around my kin's sword blade, oily black

03:05:23.140 --> 03:05:27.060
 smoke pouring from the open wound of its neck.

03:05:27.060 --> 03:05:32.940
 A winged creature formed in the air above him and screamed wordless hatred at him, then

03:05:32.940 --> 03:05:36.500
 the wind caught it, and it was gone.

03:05:36.500 --> 03:05:40.540
 Making sagged, Albin's hand reaching out to steady him.

03:05:40.540 --> 03:05:46.260
 "There's no getting used to that," McKean breathed, as he yanked his swords free of

03:05:46.260 --> 03:05:49.060
 the creature's corpse.

03:05:49.060 --> 03:05:54.500
 He looked around, saw more of the demon forms appearing in the air above them and then evaporating.

03:05:54.500 --> 03:06:00.920
 At a glance, it seemed that most of those Khadashim that had attacked them had fallen,

03:06:00.920 --> 03:06:06.020
 though many of McKean's and Albin's men were lying still and silent upon the ground.

03:06:06.020 --> 03:06:12.620
 As McKean watched, Alsion, Rayna, and Tane dispatched the last Khadashim.

03:06:12.620 --> 03:06:15.700
 "Gandal," McKean breathed.

03:06:15.700 --> 03:06:20.740
 "Down there," Albin gestured.

03:06:20.740 --> 03:06:25.160
 McKean saw the King of Khanna Tane disappearing amongst the tents, far more Khadashim still

03:06:25.160 --> 03:06:28.200
 about him than McKean had hoped to see.

03:06:28.200 --> 03:06:30.340
 Two men were moving with them.

03:06:30.340 --> 03:06:34.500
 One of them paused as the others disappeared from view and looked back for a moment McKean's

03:06:34.500 --> 03:06:36.540
 eyes locked with him.

03:06:36.540 --> 03:06:40.260
 He staggered, felt as if he'd just been punched in the gut.

03:06:40.260 --> 03:06:46.940
 "It cannot be," McKean's heart was suddenly pounding in his chest, a wave of shock spilling

03:06:46.940 --> 03:06:48.740
 into fury.

03:06:48.740 --> 03:06:53.740
 "Jale,"

03:06:53.740 --> 03:06:55.740
 Chapter 12

03:06:55.740 --> 03:06:58.740
 Jale

03:06:58.740 --> 03:07:02.660
 Jale stood and stared at the warriors on the hill.

03:07:02.660 --> 03:07:08.460
 One man had emerged ahead of the others, blood soaked, and battle grim, a shortsword in each

03:07:08.460 --> 03:07:10.260
 hand.

03:07:10.260 --> 03:07:14.660
 He was staring back at Jale, and although they were a good hundred paces apart, Jale

03:07:14.660 --> 03:07:19.140
 was certain he saw a hatred twist the man's features.

03:07:19.140 --> 03:07:22.780
 There is something familiar about him.

03:07:22.780 --> 03:07:26.900
 "My lord," Dag said, "putting at his sleeve.

03:07:26.900 --> 03:07:29.580
 We must keep moving."

03:07:29.580 --> 03:07:33.420
 They were following the Jihad that was shepherding Gandal, and his retinue of lackeys

03:07:33.420 --> 03:07:38.420
 to safety, hoping that the Jihad would guard Jale and Dag as well as the others as they

03:07:38.420 --> 03:07:41.300
 passed through the camp.

03:07:41.300 --> 03:07:45.340
 Jale had heard the sounds of battle from the hilltop and paused to watch the bloody work

03:07:45.340 --> 03:07:49.500
 of the handful of Jihad warriors that had remained behind.

03:07:49.500 --> 03:07:55.480
 They had fallen, but then it was a score against close to two hundred, and even so the

03:07:55.480 --> 03:07:59.020
 Jihad had decimated their enemy.

03:07:59.020 --> 03:08:05.220
 As Jale stared, he saw the man burst into motion running hard towards him screaming Jale's

03:08:05.220 --> 03:08:06.220
 name.

03:08:06.220 --> 03:08:08.260
 "He knows me."

03:08:08.260 --> 03:08:09.660
 Jale took an involuntary step back.

03:08:10.660 --> 03:08:12.660
 "It doesn't seem to like me much, though."

03:08:12.660 --> 03:08:13.660
 "Who?"

03:08:13.660 --> 03:08:15.660
 Then he knew.

03:08:15.660 --> 03:08:16.860
 "My King."

03:08:16.860 --> 03:08:21.900
 He had changed almost beyond all recognition, slimmer than Jale remembered him.

03:08:21.900 --> 03:08:28.460
 His body chiseled, arms and legs a striated mass of muscle, face a place of ridges, scars

03:08:28.460 --> 03:08:31.900
 and hate-filled eyes.

03:08:31.900 --> 03:08:34.300
 How is he here?

03:08:34.300 --> 03:08:38.500
 He should be dead, or at least a thousand leagues from here, and in shackles.

03:08:39.500 --> 03:08:44.420
 Jale remembered the last time he had seen Makin on the bridge at Dunkelon, chained and

03:08:44.420 --> 03:08:49.220
 being dragged away by Lycos to a Vinfallen slave ship.

03:08:49.220 --> 03:08:54.900
 The fool had challenged me to the court of swords, insulted me in front of my men.

03:08:54.900 --> 03:09:00.340
 From the look on Makin's face, that court of swords was still high on his agenda.

03:09:00.340 --> 03:09:02.180
 Jale gulped.

03:09:02.180 --> 03:09:06.180
 If Makin's expression did not convince him that he was time to go, the warriors charging

03:09:06.180 --> 03:09:09.220
 down the hill behind Makin did.

03:09:09.220 --> 03:09:12.260
 There were giants amongst him.

03:09:12.260 --> 03:09:17.220
 This way, Dagg snapped at him as they entered a maze of tents.

03:09:17.220 --> 03:09:22.020
