 Raven's and crows. Uphas muttered as he trudged through the marshland,

04:20:10.580 --> 04:20:16.580
 eyes looking skyward. He stumbled, his foot sinking with a splash into a

04:20:16.580 --> 04:20:20.660
 patch of soft ground. And he leaned on his spear to leave himself upright.

04:20:20.660 --> 04:20:25.380
 Salak, his shieldman, reached out to steadying hand from behind him.

04:20:25.380 --> 04:20:28.740
 Marshland is not a good place for a giant to walk.

04:20:28.740 --> 04:20:35.780
 What's that? Rin said. She was sitting in the stern of a large boat,

04:20:35.780 --> 04:20:38.820
 surrounded by a score of warriors as well as half a dozen rowers.

04:20:38.820 --> 04:20:44.980
 Uphas was picking apart alongside the banks of the waterways she was being rowed down,

04:20:44.980 --> 04:20:48.100
 a line of the Nothi giant spread out along the bank behind him.

04:20:48.100 --> 04:20:56.100
 Raven's uncrows. Uphas repeated, stopping and pointing up at the sky to where a black shape spiraled

04:20:56.100 --> 04:21:03.780
 higher above them. And what about them? Rin asked. She was in an unusually good mood this morning,

04:21:03.780 --> 04:21:08.260
 the first that Uphas had seen since she had learned of her war bands to feet in the marshes

04:21:08.260 --> 04:21:10.500
 and of the death of her huntsman, brave.

04:21:11.460 --> 04:21:16.980
 "I don't like them," Uphas grumbled, thinking of feck in the marons treacherous raven.

04:21:16.980 --> 04:21:24.500
 Rin stared up at the speck in the sky. "I've always rather light them," she said,

04:21:24.500 --> 04:21:28.740
 "and I suppose this one's a speck that will be providing its dinner."

04:21:28.740 --> 04:21:35.140
 Uphas scowled up at the bird. "I, as long as it's not her eyeballs and innards that it is

04:21:35.140 --> 04:21:42.500
 feasting upon." He looked around him. More boats filled the waterway, bursting with over a thousand

04:21:42.500 --> 04:21:48.980
 warriors. Not likely that will be losing this battle, he thought. Looking at the grim faces of men

04:21:48.980 --> 04:21:52.980
 in every boat, bristling with iron and the fifty Benothi warriors behind him.

04:21:52.980 --> 04:21:56.980
 More than enough to put down this little uprising.

04:21:56.980 --> 04:22:01.220
 But since they had left the tower at the marshland's edge,

04:22:01.220 --> 04:22:05.700
 a down mood had fallen across Uphas's shoulders like a heavy cloak and he could not shake it.

04:22:05.700 --> 04:22:10.820
 We should be getting on with the important business of finding Evanis and the necklace,

04:22:10.820 --> 04:22:15.700
 that is all that matters. Because when they found Namans necklace,

04:22:15.700 --> 04:22:20.580
 one of the seven treasures, then Uphas would be one huge step closer to achieving his dream.

04:22:20.580 --> 04:22:28.180
 King of the Giants. No more clans, no more divisions, just my kin behind me.

04:22:29.460 --> 04:22:36.180
 But first, I must find the necklace. Then it is to down and on Terrace to find the cup and then.

04:22:36.180 --> 04:22:42.580
 He's all brave for peer up ahead, moving smoothly across the ground. He's two hounds with him.

04:22:42.580 --> 04:22:48.740
 He ran across the marshland towards them, hardly glancing at where he was putting his feet.

04:22:48.740 --> 04:22:52.740
 Everything about the lads screamed vitality.

04:22:54.580 --> 04:23:00.180
 Uphas robbed at the small of his back and frowned. There is something about him,

