 To be away from this danger, the daily fear of being discovered in court,

04:56:15.460 --> 04:56:20.020
 but being away from our den, which has kept us safe and hidden a whole moon.

04:56:21.940 --> 04:56:27.540
 "And, talking of being discovered, I should go back to the hospice as the sun will be rising."

04:56:27.540 --> 04:56:32.500
 Sif squeezed her harder and Cohen squeezed her in return.

04:56:32.500 --> 04:56:39.460
 "I cannot tell you how happy I am to know that you're alive in here," Coen said.

04:56:39.460 --> 04:56:40.260
 "And my boot I?"

04:56:40.260 --> 04:56:43.140
 She hugged the hound's neck, kissing him.

04:56:43.140 --> 04:56:47.860
 "I'll return soon," she said, then made her goodbyes,

04:56:47.860 --> 04:56:50.100
 ruffling the cubs' heads and hugging Sif again.

04:56:51.460 --> 04:56:55.140
 She gave boot I a stern order to stay and then backed into the darkness of the tunnel.

04:56:55.140 --> 04:56:59.380
 Boot I wind, but he did not follow her.

04:56:59.380 --> 04:57:04.340
 Halen did, though, and soon they were at the slope that led up to the courtyard.

04:57:04.340 --> 04:57:06.420
 Moonlight showed them the way.

04:57:06.420 --> 04:57:13.460
 "That's smell," Cohen said, wrinkling her nose of these stood in the darkness at the base of the

04:57:13.460 --> 04:57:18.020
 slope. She was staring into the darkness of the tunnel where the smell was drifting from.

04:57:19.140 --> 04:57:22.740
 "I recognize it," she said quietly, her expression changing.

04:57:22.740 --> 04:57:24.660
 She looked scared.

04:57:24.660 --> 04:57:27.700
 "Is that another tunnel?" she asked him.

04:57:27.700 --> 04:57:32.580
 "It is," he said, remembering the first time he'd found this place,

04:57:32.580 --> 04:57:35.540
 how he'd crawled that way first, eventually stopping and coming back.

04:57:35.540 --> 04:57:40.500
 It gets too narrow. Strangely, the cubs never went that way.

04:57:40.500 --> 04:57:44.660
 "Good," Coen said, her expression relaxing.

04:57:45.940 --> 04:57:51.860
 "Why?" "Because I know that smell, and I think there are dregs down there."

04:57:51.860 --> 04:57:56.980
 Chapter 22

04:57:56.980 --> 04:57:58.660
 Corbin

04:57:58.660 --> 04:58:06.980
 Corbin sat upon a giant bear, hands gripping the high palm of a saddle as it shambled along

04:58:06.980 --> 04:58:11.140
 a fresh-built road that cut like a spear through the trees and undergrowth of form.

04:58:12.580 --> 04:58:17.220
 Jail's road, which he built almost from the boundaries of Graham's hold to see him in his war band

04:58:17.220 --> 04:58:24.580
 to the walls of Jassel. The bear's pace was surprisingly fast, eating up the leagues at a relentless

04:58:24.580 --> 04:58:30.660
 pace throughout each day's travel. His legs were aching, the girth of a bear was unsuitable for

04:58:30.660 --> 04:58:35.620
 his human legs. "I miss shield," he thought. "Not for the first time."

04:58:35.620 --> 04:58:42.340
 The trees were thinning now, the terrain changing and more sunlight breaking through the canopy

04:58:42.340 --> 04:58:47.620
 above. There was less vine and thorn on the ground, more grass and wildflowers.

04:58:47.620 --> 04:58:53.700
 And then, Corbin saw the stumps of trees, a whole veil harvested of timber.

04:58:53.700 --> 04:59:02.020
 We are close to Graham's hold. With every league that he had travelled, every day that had passed,

04:59:02.020 --> 04:59:07.540
 he had felt his spirit sink. After Michael's revelation about the prophecy,

04:59:07.540 --> 04:59:12.260
 Corbin had been in the deepest depths of despair, but focusing on the hope of

04:59:12.260 --> 04:59:16.420
 being reunited with Coen and his friends had given him the strength to endure.

04:59:16.420 --> 04:59:19.700
 It had been something to live for, to fight for.

04:59:19.700 --> 04:59:26.740
 Now he knew that, with every breath that he drew, he was being taken further away from them,

04:59:26.740 --> 04:59:30.260
 if they still lived, and despondency had morphed into anger.

04:59:30.260 --> 04:59:39.220
 Hated faces appeared in his mind, Caledas, Nefair, Ealdair, Rin, Michael.

04:59:40.820 --> 04:59:45.700
 He had thought about escape, but the simple truth was that even if he could somehow break

04:59:45.700 --> 04:59:49.940
 his bonds and slip away from his giant captors, he would not have been able to walk half

04:59:49.940 --> 04:59:56.100
 the league because of his injuries. Even now, over a moon from when he'd been captured,

04:59:56.100 --> 05:00:00.180
 they were still not fully recovered. Soon, no, perhaps.

